title: apple bread
directions: Mix
together
in
order
given.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf
pans and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Steam cabbage in pot for 10 to 15 minutes and carefully separate leaves.
Mix meat, onion, pepper, saltines, ketchup and egg until well blended.
Take meat mixture and make 3 inch balls. Wrap in cabbage leaves and arrange in large pot.
Pour tomato juice and tomato sauce over top.
Cook on medium 1 1/2 hours.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Spread ice cream evenly onto bottom of crust.
Place in freezer until firm.
Spread caramel sauce over ice cream.
Sprinkle with peanuts and cover with whipped topping.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all three ingredients in large mixing bowl. Mix well and form into bite-size balls. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: elvera's fairy pie
directions: Make pastry for two-crust pie.

title: white corn casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium size saucepan, on low heat, mix together oleo, cream cheese and milk until melted. Add remaining ingredients. Place mixture in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Heat in oven until bubbly.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Mix the baked cornbread with the package of herb stuffing mix and set aside.
In saucepan, combine the butter, chopped celery, onions, water, salt and black pepper.
Cook until tender.
Combine with dry mixture along with eggs and stock from turkey or chicken to moisten as needed.
Place in large, buttered baking pan and bake in a 300° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Stir in other ingredients and bake at 350° in unbaked pie shell until firm.
Heat may be reduced.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fry on hot, lightly greased pan. Flip when brown; fry 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Keep warm in oven. Delicious with applesauce.
Great side dish for pork.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Saute beef, onions and celery in fat for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles and turn into casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle noodles on top 10 minutes before removing from oven.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Halfway through baking, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into bars.
Serves 6.

title: easy white frosting
directions: Put margarine and powdered sugar in mixing bowl; mix well. Add vanilla and milk.
Beat on medium until smooth.

title: chicken and asparagus au gratin
directions: Mix bread cubes with cheese and 1/4 cup of the melted butter. Line a 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch dish with half of the bread cubes. Arrange asparagus on cubes.
Melt remaining butter over flame, blend in flour, salt and pepper, then add milk, stirring until well mixed.
Cook until thick.
Add chicken and pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle top with rest of bread cubes and cheese mix. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until brown.
Serves 8.

title: quiche
directions: In a small bowl, grate cheese.
Set aside.
Brush pie crust with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown. Remove from heat and cool.
In a bowl, slice
sausages into fifths. Stir in eggs and beat.
Stir in milk and seasonings.
Blend flour with grated cheese.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven until knife comes out clean when inserted into center.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato relish
directions: Put salt over tomatoes and let stand an hour or more. Wash tomatoes.
Drain well.
Heat to boiling point.
Don't boil.
Seal in hot jars.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in jar.
Use 4 tablespoons per 1 cup of hot water.

title: tomato vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender on medium to high speed 25 seconds.
Will keep refrigerated 2 days.
Shake before using. Makes 1/3 cup.

title: punch for 100
directions: In 6 gallon container, combine water, sugar, soft drink mix, orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice and apricot nectar.
Mix well.
Just before serving, pour 1/3 of punch mixture into a punch bowl.
Add 1 bottle ginger ale as bowl empties.
Repeat with remaining punch mixture and ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage and onion in casserole dish.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over the top.
Combine egg, soup and mayonnaise; pour over top.
Combine crackers, 1/4 cup butter and cheese; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and greens pot pie
directions: Saute ham in hot oil in a Dutch oven over medium high heat 5 minutes or until lightly browned. Add flour and cook, stirring constantly 1 minute. Gradually add chicken broth and cook stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until broth begins to thicken. Bring mixture to a boil and add seasoning blend and collard greens. Return to a boil and cook, stirring often, 15 minutes. Stir in black eyed peas and crushed red pepper. Spoon hot mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Pour Cornbread Crust Batter evenly over hot filling mixture. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cornbread is golden brown and set.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
That's all; just enjoy.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in lengthwise slices about 1/2-inch thick. In a greased 2-quart casserole, arrange layers as follows: apples, brown sugar, nuts and seasoning.
Dot each layer with butter. Repeat layering process until casserole is full or ingredients are used up.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pear preserves
directions: Add 1/2 sugar to water and boil 2 minutes.
Add pears and boil 15 minutes.
Add remaining sugar and lemon.
Cook until fruit is tender and clear.
Let stand several hours.
Strain.
Pack cold fruit into hot jars.
Boil syrup until thick as honey.
Pour hot syrup over pears.
Seal.

title: egg souffle
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Remove crusts from bread.
Cut into cubes. Beat eggs; add milk and seasonings.
Stir in bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour into oblong 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until center is set.
Serves 10.
May be mixed the night before you serve it.

title: rose's party cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese together when soft.
Chill to harden.
Then shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Garnish with stemmed cherry or parsley sprig.
Serve with crackers.

title: crispy apple dessert
directions: Place apples in 8-inch square pan.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and remaining ingredients.
Blend until mixed and crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Delicious warm but can be served cold.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Then add sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spread on cookie sheet lined with flour and greased wax paper.
Top with nutmeats.
Bake.

title: tangy tomato aspic
directions: Heat 2 cups V-8 juice and dissolve gelatin in hot juice.
Add remaining V-8 juice and olives.
Pour into a lightly oiled 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: cranberried sweet potatoes
directions: 1. Combine all ingredients with the exception of the sweet potatoes and mix well.
2. Cut sweet potatoes in half and remove several Tbsps. of
pulp from the center of each half.
3. Fill hollowed potatoes with cranberry mixture. Sprinkle
with additional brown sugar for a shinny glaze.
4. Place potatoes under broiler until hot and bubbling.
Serve at once.

title: chili pepper potato salad
directions: In large bowl, toss potatoes, sweet pepper and peas.
In blender, combine salad dressing, chili peppers, salt, pepper and garlic.
Blend until smooth.
Toss with potato mixture.
Chill.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Put 1 wafer into each baking cup.
Combine cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with a spoonful of pie filling.

title: nancy's french market soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix.
Place in Dutch oven and cover with water to 2-inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans and add 2 quarts water, ham hock, salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove ham hock from soup.
Remove meat from bone.
Chop meat and return to soup.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: dutch slaw(for a crowd)
directions: Chop all vegetables together.
Sprinkle sugar over top without stirring.
Heat vinegar, salt, mustard and celery seed to boiling. Then add vegetable oil and heat again.
Pour over chopped vegetables.
But do not stir.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot mexican salsa
directions: Use blender or food processor; add all ingredients.
Blend until chunky.
Cover and chill.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onions with margarine; add bread cubes and toss together.
Place half of tomatoes in small casserole dish.
Layer half of bread mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
A nice recipe for home canned tomatoes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Continue baking at 350° for 30 minutes or until set. Tastes like sugar cream pie.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, garlic, salt, Tabasco sauce and pepper.
Cook and simmer 20 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 11 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Put 3/4 of noodles in casserole.
Add all of meat mixture and chopped onions on top.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with yeast.
Stir water, milk, butter, sugar and salt together and cook over a low heat until butter melts. Cool 5 minutes.
Add flour and yeast, remaining flour, nuts, raisins and eggs.
Dough will be stiff.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Divide dough in half and place half in each of 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Cover with lid and let rise in warm place until dough is 1-inch from the top.
Remove lid and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: mrs. patterson's butternut pie
directions: Cut outer skin away from squash.
Cut
in pieces.
Cook inside meat by boiling on stove until soft.
Remove and drain. Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, sugar, flavorings and milk. Mix until lumps are gone.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake
at
350° to 375° until firm.

title: quick spicy chicken salad
directions: Mix dressing, honey, jalapeno pepper, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sance and red pepper.
Arrange chicken over lettuce.
Top with tomatoes and mushrooms.
Drizzle with dressing mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine lemon juice and next 5 ingredients.
Pour over bean mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley and stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all together with real mayonnaise.

title: smoked sausage with cabbage, sweet potatoes and apple
directions: Stir chicken broth and mustard in deep 12-inch skillet until blended.
Stir in mustard seed.
Bring to boil over high heat. Add potatoes and onion; reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes, shaking pan occasionally, until potatoes are almost tender.
Add cabbage and sausage.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes longer, stirring once or twice, until potatoes are tender and cabbage is crisp-tender.
Stir in apple.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes until apple is crisp-tender.
Serves 4.
(Good with rye bread.)

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in casserole dish. Top with crushed crackers. Drizzle butter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Spread 1 cup whip topping in bottom of pie crust.
Freeze for 10 minutes.
Carefully spoon jam over whip topping.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat well 1 to 2 minutes the pudding mix, milk and peanut butter.
Fold in remaining whip topping.
Spoon over jam in pie crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with additional whip topping and chopped nuts if desired.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix cherry Jell-O, sugar and hot water until dissolved. Mix all ingredients and freeze.
When getting ready to serve, defrost until it
makes
a mushy mixture.
Add about 20 ounces ginger ale and
tablespoons
sherbet.
Mix
until mushy and serve.
Serves 30.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine and pat into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mash bananas with mixer.
Add all ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Bake for approximately 1 hour.
Turn out and cool. Freezes well!!

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla flavoring.
Break up bread in chunks; add melted butter and 2 cups of milk.
Mix all together.
Bake in baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add margarine, milk and mustard.
Beat by hand. Fold in grated cheese, cubed bread and ham.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: garlic cheese log
directions: Combine cheeses until smooth, using mixer or blender.
Add garlic and salt; mix well.
Shape into 2 logs and roll in poppy seed to coat.
Chill and serve.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until light and foamy in large bowl.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and margarine until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture and mix at low speed until blended. Stir in nuts at low speed.
Mixture will be stiff.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into 2 dozen bars.

title: lazy woman's cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and beat 100 strokes.
Add 1 cup boiling water over crock and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then decrease to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir until moistened. Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: "oh so good" casserole
directions: Brown onion, celery, pepper and beef in butter.
Mix rice, soups, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Mix altogether.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with shredded cheese and shoestring potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This will serve 10 people.

title: lemon lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine flour, butter and walnuts; blend well.
Pat mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.
Let cool.
In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup of the whipped topping; blend well.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly onto cooled crust pan.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together sour cream, soup and sherry.
Mix well.
Add washed mushrooms and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with wild rice or fried brown rice.

title: tomato quiche
directions: Roll pie dough to fit an 8-inch pie pan and 1/2 inch up sides of pan.
Brush with soft or melted margarine.
Peel tomatoes; cut in wedges and arrange, overlapping, over entire crust.
Sprinkle with Jane's salt and any herbs you like.
Mix together onion, mayonnaise (or your preferred version), yogurt and cheese.
Spread over tomatoes.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 20 minutes at 350° or until fully baked and set firm.
Should be served warm.

title: french chicken
directions: Place chicken in a crock-pot.
Pour French dressing over chicken.
Add dry soup mix.
Cook all day on low heat.

title: white icing
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Add flour and milk.
Beat 10 to 15 minutes with mixer.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Grease
a 2-quart baking dish.
Place chips in bottom.
Layer chicken next.
Heat soups, Ro-Tel and milk and pour mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: glorious chicken casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 tortillas and 1/2 chicken in an 8 x 8-inch dish. Repeat.
In a saucepan, combine flour, salt, bouillon and ketchup. Blend in milk gradually.
Heat, stirring, until thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir in mushrooms, chilies and onion flakes; pour over chicken and tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 1/2
hours.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Chop meat in blender, along with onion.
Mix together other ingredients.
Set aside half of the pressed meat.
Make into a large ball.
Roll in remainder of beef. Chill.

title: blue cheese-scallion dip
directions: Pulse sour cream and Blue cheese in food processor with on-off motions until creamy (maybe slightly lumpy). Remove to bowl. Stir in scallions, salt and pepper. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour for the flavor to develop. Serve with raw or blanched vegetables.

title: barley pilaf
directions: Saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter 4 to 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms; saute a few more minutes and remove from pan.
Brown barley in remainder of butter, stirring often.
Put in casserole; add onions and mushrooms, salt and 2 cups chicken stock.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining stock; stir and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Serves 10.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and drain; mash. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic. Beat at high speed until smooth. Stir in chives. Put in lightly greased 2 1/2-quart dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix by hand until blended; bake 55 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pickled beets and onion rings
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add beets and onion rings.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until hot and onions are tender, about 15 minutes.

title: quick bean soup
directions: In a 2-quart pot (or larger), add oil, onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add carrot, potato, salt, pepper, chicken broth, water and ketchup; cook until tender.
Pour 1 can of the beans in a blender or mash.
Pour all the beans into the pot with other ingredients.
Stir well.
Add more liquid, if needed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crushed pineapple pie
directions: If using pineapple, use no sugar.
I did not use any sugar.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine melted butter, confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs and press into dish.
Mix Dream Whip, cold milk and salt until forms peaks.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, vanilla and cream cheese mixture.
Combine this with Dream Whip mixture and mix well. Spread over crumbs and top with 1 can of cherry pie filling.
Chill for 6 hours.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and pineapple and put in casserole (8 x 11-inch).
Mix together Ritz crackers, oleo and Cheddar cheese and place on top of pineapple.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes (1/2 recipe, 4 good servings).

title: turkey taco salad
directions: Prepare ground turkey according to seasoning directions.
Add corn.
Make a salad with remaining ingredients.
Combine seasoned meat with salad mixture.
Garnish with sour cream, salsa and avocado.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread as thin as possible on 12x18 cookie sheet (jelly roll pan).
Brush with egg white, pouring off excess.
Cover with 1/2 to 1 c.
finely chopped pecans.
Press into cookie dough.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until vegetables are coated.
Empty bag into shallow baking pan and discard bag. Bake; stir once for about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: turkey noodle bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lori's tuna spinach loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole with oil.
Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Place in casserole pan, then in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, let sit for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: play doh
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook in saucepan, on low heat, stirring constantly.
Let cool after mixture follows wooden spoon around pan.
While still warm, knead dough on waxed paper until color is thoroughly mixed through dough.
Put into large plastic bag or divide dough into several small plastic bags.
Resealable plastic bags work best.

title: aunt adele's lemon bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to batter and beat until smooth.
Add lemon rind and nuts.
Place in greased bread pan, about 4 x 8-inch and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While bread is baking, mix juice of 1 lemon and 1/2 cup sugar until sugar is dissolved (to make a glaze).
Spoon glaze over hot bread before removing from pan.
Continue to do so until bread has absorbed all of the glaze.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Put small amount of oats in blender at a time until it turns to a powder.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Cook chicken until tender and cut in small pieces.
Roll chicken in crescent rolls.
Place in shallow casserole.
Mix soup and milk; pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Cook ground beef and mix with taco seasoning.
In edged serving dish, layer ingredients in order listed (deep edged 9-inch pie plate works great).
Serve with corn chips.

title: deviled ham dip for crackers
directions: Stir together; refrigerate. Serve on crackers.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Combine ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Batter is real stiff.

title: triple-action multi-purpose cleaner(helpful hint)
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bucket.
A more dilute solution can be made by halving the amount of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Store this cleaner in a clean bottle and use as needed.

title: super vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in large saucepan, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add juice, vegetables, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: marinade for flank steak or boneless skinless chicken breasts
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add oil and onion (if desired).
Pour marinade over meat and let marinate 4 hours or longer, even overnight.
Turn pieces occasionally.
Barbecue or bake according to meat directions.
Five minutes each side for medium-rare flank steaks; 10 minutes each side for boneless, skinless chicken breasts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fresh broccoli may also be used.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Place warm water in bowl; add yeast and sugar.
Let set 10 minutes.
Blend flour, dry milk, baking powder and salt in mixer bowl.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add yeast mixture and knead lightly.
Roll out as for biscuits; cut in rounds.
Place on greased pans and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in 425° oven about 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: quiche
directions: Grate cheese and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients (except pie crust) and add to cheese.
Pour in uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 1 (9-inch) quiche.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil jello, pudding and water. Cool. Drain fruit. Fold in cooled jello. Chill. Serve.

title: sausage fingers
directions: Lightly brown sausage links.
Open biscuits and pat out each one to about a 3-inch circle.
Roll 1 sausage link in center of each biscuit with meat ends showing about 1/2-inch on each end, seal by pressing biscuit together.
On cookie sheet, bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with butter and picante sauce.

title: doritos chicken
directions: Crush the Doritos just enough to cover the bottom of a 2 quart baking dish.
Mix the chicken, sour cream, chili powder, salt and garlic powder and place all this on top of the Doritos.
Crush a little bit more Doritos and sprinkle on top.
Then last, sprinkle on the cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with picante sauce over the top.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and lemon juice until smooth.
Fold in topping, fruit and pecans.
Pour into shells and refrigerate.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook bacon slices until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Leave 3 tablespoons bacon fat in skillet.
Saute onions in bacon fat until golden and soft.
Add wine and cook until wine evaporates. Beat together eggs, butter, cream, Parmesan and parsley.
Add onions.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water as directed on package.
Transfer with slotted spoon to large warmed bowl.
Add egg-and-cheese mixture and toss.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top.
Grind black pepper over all and serve.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Separate eggs and drop yolks into creamed mixture. (Put whites aside.) Beat thoroughly. Add half of flour with half of yogurt; mix, then add balance of flour, yogurt and soda. Add pineapple and vanilla. Beat about 3 minutes; whip egg whites and fold into batter. Spoon into Bundt cake pan and bake about 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°. Cool and cover with Pineapple Glaze or your favorite icing.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a heated waffle iron.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, celery salt, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with mixture and refrigerate overnight, uncovered or light cover.
Next day, roll chicken in bread crumbs and arrange in shallow baking pan.
Spoon half of the butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Spoon remaining butter over chicken and bake 15 minutes longer. Serve hot.
Leftovers are delicious cold.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Saute ground beef, peppers and onions together.
Cook rice, following package directions.
Add rice, tomato sauce, tomatoes and 3 ounces of cheese to dish.
Cook, stirring, until the cheese melts.
tags: Healthy Choice extra lean ground beef

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and set aside (cool with cold water).
Dice tomato, green pepper, cucumber and onion.
Add to cooled spaghetti.
Add McCormick seasoning and celery seed to 8 ounces Kraft Free Italian dressing.
Pour over spaghetti and vegetable mixture.
Toss to mix.
Chill for several hours.
(You may need to add more dressing before serving.)

title: cardamon bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water with 1 tablespoon sugar; set aside 5 to 10 minutes or until foamy.
Scald milk and add remaining sugar, margarine and salt.
When margarine has melted, remove from heat, cool to lukewarm and add spices.
Combine with yeast mixture and gradually stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead for 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl, turn to grease bottom and cover.
Let set 1 1/2 hours or until elastic and smooth.
Place in baking pan which has been buttered or oiled.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Boil 1 cup water; add 1/2 cup shortening and set aside 30 minutes.
Sprinkle yeast over 1/4 cup lukewarm water; let stand 30 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar and salt and make a well in middle. Mix water with shortening and yeast water with egg and pour into well.
Beat hard until smooth and shiny.
Let rise 2 hours in unheated oven.
Knead and shape into rolls and let rise 2 hours. Bake at 400°.
Can bake until very light brown and freeze for later use.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: lemon snowflakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls and put chopped nuts on top of balls.
Press with a glass to flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cake mix with eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in the nuts.
Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Centers will be soft.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Add to mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.

title: smoothest chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together pieces of chocolate bars, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.

title: vadai
directions: Soak the yellow split peas in warm water for 2 to 3 hours. Chop the onion and peppers into tiny pieces.
Crush the bay leaves.
Drain the peas and grind them in the blender (without adding water) to form a coarse paste.
Mix salt, onion, peppers, crushed pepper, crushed bay leaves and the paste thoroughly.
Shape the mixture into balls of 1-inch diameter and flatten them.
Heat the oil for deep frying and fry the flattened balls in the oil. Take them out when they turn to golden brown and spread them on sheets of paper towels.
These Vadais are good snacks for parties.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Make your own baked pie shell or use a butter ready crust. If you use the latter, some of the filling will be left over. Just pour it into a dessert dish, chill and enjoy it yourself.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except tomatoes in skillet; heat until cheese
melts.
Beat
until cool.
Stuff tomatoes about 3/4 full and bake in a 375° oven until filling browns.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Prepare all ingredients ahead of time.
Marinate chicken breast strips in soy sauce and garlic mixture of water, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Heat wok and put in oil; swirl to coat.
Cook chicken until white.
Remove.
Cook carrots a few minutes, then add broccoli.
(Add oil, water or 1/2 cup bouillon or broth, if needed.) Stir-fry until broccoli begins to get tender (bright green).
Then add onion.
Stir-fry a few more minutes.
Then add mushrooms and soy sauce mixture.
Stir until thickened (2 to 3 minutes).
Serve over hot rice.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once. Beat 2 to 3 minutes. Grease and flour small Bundt pan or oblong pan. Spray with nonstick spray, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: skillet meal(italian style)
directions: Brown beef with garlic powder in a large skillet.
Drain off fat; stir in tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and seasonings. Spread cottage cheese over sauce.
Cover with macaroni and cover with stewed tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and cook 5 minutes more.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Grate cheese.
Wash and deseed chillies.
Drain on paper towel.
In casserole dish, 7 x 11-inch, layer chillies and cheese. Whip cold milk until it forms peaks.
Add egg and whip again. Add flour a little at a time while whipping.
Pour over chillies-cheese mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread can of tomato sauce over top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: confetti baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick each with a fork and bake in a hot oven at 450° about 45 minutes.
Cut slice from top of each potato and scoop out center, being careful not to break skins.
Add milk, 1/4 cup oleo or butter, salt and pepper to hot pulp and mash until light.

title: honey apple pork chops
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in shallow dish.
Mix well.
Add pork chops.
Marinate covered in refrigerator over night turning chops occasionally.
Drain reservings.
Marinate.
Grill chops or bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Add cream cheese until all is smooth.
Place around edge of shell.
Pour pie mix in center.

title: yummy 7-layer bean dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer ingredients in order given in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: Mix crackers, margarine and sugar well.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs well.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Pour pie filling on top of cooled pie. Refrigerate a few hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: grammi's chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Fold in the sour cream and soup.
Spread the stuffing mix on top.
Dot the top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Grind and serve on crackers, celery or apple slices.

title: cheese straws
directions: Add melted butter to grated cheese.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cheese mixture.
Knead well.
Bake in 350° oven, but do not brown.

title: summer lemon butter cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions.
While still warm, poke several holes all over cake. Melt butter, powdered sugar and enough lemon juice to taste and to make it easy to drizzle.
Pour over cake. Refrigerate.

title: cherry soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine cherries, water, wine, cinnamon stick and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until fruit is soft, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sugar and orange rind and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove cinnamon stick and cloves and discard.
Puree cherry mixture in blender.
Pour back into pan and stir in arrowroot, mixed with a little of the fruit mixture. Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
Serve hot with dumplings or ice cold with dollop of whipped cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs and pineapple. Crumble bread into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (no lid) in a greased casserole dish.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Blend in flour, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir in milk, broth and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sauce is thick.
Fold in chicken and Veg-All.
Pour in lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with biscuit dough rolled out or you can make your own dough and bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese tip casserole
directions: Alternate layers of bread and cheese in buttered casserole. Over this pour lightly beaten eggs mixed with milk, salt and mustard.
Place in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Bake in 300° oven 1 hour or until done.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over low heat in boiler until liquid is gone.
Stir constantly.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: fricasseed rabbit
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Wash rabbits thoroughly.
Pat dry. Cut
into pieces, discarding bony rib section.
In Dutch oven, melt
butter
and shortening over medium-high heat.
Mix beaten eggs with 1 tablespoon water.
Dip rabbit in egg.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Brown rabbit, turning until all sides are evenly browned.
Add
water to cover and onions.
Cover.
Bake about 2 hours or until tender.
Remove onions.
Add dumplings. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Cook and stir milk, orange juice and marshmallows over medium heat until marshmallows melt. Remove from heat and stir in all fruits until well blended. Mix crumbs and spices and stir into fruit mixture. Press firmly into loaf pan or ring mold. Refrigerate. Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: hanky panky spread
directions: Brown drain and crumble the sausage and ground chuck.
Melt the cheese; add the mustard and garlic powder, then stir this into the two meats.
Put in a fondue or food warmer pot; place party bread around it.
Keep warm; spread and enjoy.

title: noky(small dumplings)
directions: Beat together egg, milk, salt and flour; mix well.
Put batter onto a plate, slicing batter with a knife to the edge of the plate, letting pieces fall off into a kettle of boiling, salt water.
Boil 5 to 7 minutes or until done.
Pull out of water with a slotted spoon to remove any water.
Continue to slice off more dumplings until batter is all done.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Pour berries into boiling orange juice.
Stir until all berries are popped.
Remove from heat.
Add honey, grated lemon and orange rind and orange wedges.
Blend until smoother.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tortellini and vegetables. Cook tortellini following directions.
Combine with your choice of (bite size) cooked potato, carrots and green beans, plus peas, mushroom caps, black olives and garbanzo beans.
Add oil/spice dressing to cooked tortellini and vegetables.
Stir so pieces are well coated.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours or more.

title: doobie's hungarian paprika chicken
directions: Rinse and dry chicken.
Melt butter in a heavy pan.
Cook onion in butter until onion is transparent.
Add chicken.
When chicken is browned, remove from skillet and set aside.
Mix in paprika with onion and butter.
Cook for 1 minute.
Beat together heavy cream, flour, sour cream and soup.
Add to onion mixture and cook on very low heat until slightly thickened.
Add the tomato and mushrooms.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until mushrooms are just done.
Return chicken to skillet and simmer on very low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve over hot egg noodles.

title: apple spice cake
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, salt and cloves.
Add applesauce, yogurt, egg whites and oil; blend well, using spoon. Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes. Loosen cake from sides of pan with knife.
Invert onto plate. Cover loosely with foil or wax paper.
Cool completely.
Slice and serve with Quick Yogurt Glaze.

title: diabetic pineapple cream pie
directions: Sprinkle pudding mix over pineapple. Add sour cream and mix. Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with whipped cream or topping. Chill until ready to serve.

title: simple white bread
directions: Measure water into a large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over the water.
Add dry milk, sugar, salt, oil and about 3 1/4 cups flour to make a thick batter.
Blend well.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually add remaining flour to form a very stiff dough.
Toss dough on a floured board until it's no longer sticky.
Knead until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Divide in half.
Roll dough to a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Roll up tightly with 6-inch side.
Seal the edges and ends.
Place seams down in 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Brush with butter.

title: fun frosting
directions: Mix all together.
Must be kept refrigerated after serving.

title: three layer double chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. In large bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes (top may appear wet).
Cool completely in pan.
Spread Mint Layer.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix together
and
pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Bring water to a boil and add sugar, butter, egg, vanilla, vinegar and flour.	Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into prepared pie crust and let cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a casserole dish, put one pie crust on bottom of dish. Chop or shred chicken and combine with all other ingredients. Pour in dish and top with other pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add Jiffy mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together, leaving out 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pour mixture over broccoli. Mix 1 stack Ritz crackers (crumbs) with 1/4 cup melted butter. Sprinkle Ritz crackers over mixture.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg and milk mixture, then in coating mix.
Foil line baking pan.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Place chicken, skin side down.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan. Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, eggs and sour cream together.
Beat well by hand until completely mixed.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, cocoa, cinnamon and nuts together.
This is "sugar mixture".
Pour half the cake batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with half the sugar mixture.
Swirl batter with knife.
Repeat with remaining batter and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: sally lunn
directions: Soften the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Heat milk to lukewarm and combine with yeast.
Cream butter and sugar together; add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and salt, then add to egg-butter mix. Alternate with the milk-yeast mixture.
Beat well with a wooden spoon and then turn into a buttered bowl.
Let rise in a warm place, until doubled in bulk (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Beat or knead down and put in a 3 1/2 x 10-inch ring mold or angel cake pan. Let rise again, until doubled.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 45 minutes.
Unmold and serve warm.

title: war cake
directions: In medium saucepan, mix brown sugar, 2 teaspoons hot water and shortening.
Add raisins, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil ingredients for 5 minutes after it first bubbles.
Remove and let cool completely (important).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into pans and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hamburger in a blanket
directions: Combine meat, onion, bread and egg.
Mix well and make into small hamburger patties.

title: corn and crabmeat chowder
directions: Fry bacon, saving drippings.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and butter to some of the drippings.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add corn, soup, garlic, stock and carrots.
Simmer 1-1/2
hours; then add crabmeat and half & half. Simmer 30 minutes longer.
Add seasonings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and spread in baking dish. Arrange tortillas over meat and onion.
Mix soups together and spoon over tortillas.
Spread the enchilada sauce over soup. Sprinkle with green chilies and top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat until ingredients are thoroughly mixed and mixture has smooth consistency.
Add vinegar and lemon extract.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Cream margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each addition. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately to batter with buttermilk. Add flavorings and beat well. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then add 1/2 of glaze.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple, dry Jell-O and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Cool and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spiced fresh fruit salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine jicama, oranges, pineapple, orange juice, confectioners sugar and cinnamon.
Refrigerate one hour, stirring occasionally.
When ready to serve, peel bananas and slice them into the salad; stir gently to mix.
Serve at once. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Prepare this 3 layer dessert in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain the salmon.
Remove bones and skin.
Flake the salmon in a large mixing bowl.
Add the remaining four ingredients to the flaked salmon and mix well.
Use your hands or an ice cream dipper to form individual croquettes.
Place a few at a time in skillet of deep hot oil (not smoking).
Cook until golden brown.
Turn only once (approximately 7) or place all of the mixture in a greased Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° until golden brown on top.

title: honey cream fruit bowl
directions: Slice bananas into large bowl.
Cover with cherries.
Peel and section grapefruit and oranges.
Mix all fruits.
Chill.
Combine sour cream, honey and salad dressing.
Add to fruit before serving.
Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: jewish chicken soup
directions: Clean and cut all vegetables into 3 to 4 inch chunks.
Clean chicken; cut into about 8 pieces.
In a large soup pot, place vegetables, garlic and onion, then chicken with dill or parsley. Add cold water until chicken is covered.
Bring to a gentle simmer and cook for 2 hours.
Skim off foam occasionally.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with rice or noodles and fresh challah bread for an authentic meal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add to milk and cream cheese.
Add corn and green chilies.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Mix everything except the egg whites.
Add them last.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and water; beat again.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add egg mixture.
Spread thin on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread the nuts and gumdrops.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: mother's best meat loaf
directions: Combine water and white bread.
When bread is soaked, crumble into meat with remaining water.
Mix in eggs, onion, seasonings and oatmeal.
Mix well.
With wet hands, shape into loaf and put into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread ketchup over top and bake 30 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour oil in a pan so it covers all of the bottom.
Dump cake mix in and add water and eggs.
Mix all in the same pan.
Smooth cake out, then add pie filling.
Smooth it all over the cake, then take a spoon and roll it over to the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas rice gumbo
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet; remove and saute onion in grease.
Add tomatoes, pepper, okra, corn, chili powder, pepper and rice; cover and simmer until rice is tender.
Place in serving dish and crumble bacon over the top.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut steak into palm size pieces.
Coat with flour mixture and brown in skillet with hot oil.
Place in covered casserole dish. Make gravy according to package directions.
Pour over steak. Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°, or until tender.

title: pizza flavored casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, garlic and seasonings, stirring to separate meat.
Combine all ingredients except cheese. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cranberry sauce, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make 2 cups.
Pour liquid into saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid in bowl.
Chill until partially set.

title: chocolate-covered peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Chill in refrigerator for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pignollata
directions: Mix the flour and salt in a bowl or on a pastry board.
Add the eggs, one by one, mixing well and kneading until the dough has a uniform consistency.
Let it stand for 30 minutes.
Take the dough, one small piece at a time and roll it between the palms of your hands into thin pencil-like strips.
With a sharp knife, cut the strips into 1/4-inch pieces, each piece should be about the size of a pea.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well; add carrots and nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: charlotte's pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions.
Drain.
Add peppers, onions, olives, cheese and dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar	together.
Add	eggs,
one at a time, beating
well.
Sift
dry	ingredients
together;	add alternately to creamed
mixture
with
lemon
extract. Stir in fruit
and	nuts.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for 1 1/2 hours in greased
and floured pans. Use an angel food pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Add oil and tomato soup.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: pink sponge salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add rice, salt, sugar and vanilla. Chill until slightly thickened; fold in Cool Whip.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and hamburger.
Pour 1/2 mushroom soup over it.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs thoroughly.
Pour into buttered casserole and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marvelous apple-n-cranberry cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs together.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into oil mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. (Dough will be stiff.)
Pour into lightly greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for an hour.
Great for Thanksgiving.
I love it because it's easy.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl and beat at low speed until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan and bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chili colorado(brian's style)
directions: Brown beef and garlic in deep iron pot.
Add onion, celery and green pepper and stir well.
Combine tomato sauce with chili powder, salt, oregano and cumin.
Stir well and add beef with tomatoes, chili salsa and jalapenos.
Fold in chili beans.
Add the beer last, without stirring.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve with hot cornbread and an icy brew!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish; put drained Veg-All on top.
Mix soup and 1/2 can chicken broth.
Pour on top of Veg-All.
Mix flour, milk and butter and put on top of other mixture.
Top with 2 cans broth.
Bake at 350° until brown (1 1/2 hours approximately).

title: broccoli and cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Blend in cheese and other ingredients.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring first five ingredients to a boil and cool.
Drain all canned vegetables well. Put all vegetables in bowl and pour oil mixture over.
Cover and let set several hours or overnight.

title: crunchy onion layered salad
directions: In a 3-quart straight-sided bowl, layer salad ingredients in order as listed.
Serve with Ranch style or your favorite salad dressing.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break vermicelli into pieces; cook according to package directions and drain.
Mix with Accent, lemon juice and oil. Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.
Add olives, pimento, mayonnaise and onions.
Mix well and refrigerate for several hours.
Must be prepared ahead.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Combine flour and next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup crust mixture and set aside. Press mixture into bottom and up sides of 9-inch quiche dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Remove crust from oven and set aside.

title: marinated arm roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over meat.
Refrigerate 3 days. Turn meat at least once.
Grill
to desired doneness.
Slice thin and serve.
My kids favorite!

title: chocolate chip piecreston, iowa
directions: Pre-heat oven to 325°.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: In saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Whisk in Jell-O and pudding mixes.
Return to boil, stirring constantly; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Fold in oranges, pineapple and whipped topping.
Spoon into a serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.

title: cheesy chicken crescents
directions: In medium pan, combine soup, milk and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour into an ungreased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Place 2 tablespoons chicken on wide end of crescent rolls and roll up.
Arrange filled rolls over hot soup mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and margarine.
Cook over medium heat until thickened (about 30 minutes).
Stir often.
Add vanilla.
Pour into serving dish.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Line a baking dish with beef.
Wrap each half of chicken in a slice of bacon.
Place in dish.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.
Cook at 300° for 3 hours (uncovered).

title: scallop lasagne
directions: Rinse scallops and drain. Melt 1/3 cup margarine in large skillet.
Add green onions, garlic and thyme.
Saute on medium-high for 1 minute.
Add scallops. Stir and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour into strainer over bowl. Let drain 20 to 30 minutes, reserving liquid in bowl.

title: lime cucumber pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminum ware. Remove sliced cucumbers from lime water.
Discard lime water. Rinse 3 times in fresh, cold water.
Soak 3 hours in fresh ice water.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and mixed pickling spices in large pot.
Bring to a low boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove syrup from heat and add sliced cucumbers.
Soak 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: marigold muffins
directions: Heat milk to boiling point.
Add crushed marigold petals. Into separate bowl, sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add oil to milk mixture.
Stir and let cool to room temperature, then add honey and egg and combine with dry ingredients.
Fill muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: rolls
directions: Put water and yeast in a bowl.
Let stand for a few minutes. Add oil.
Mix flour, salt and add to yeast mixture.
Make into a soft dough.
Knead for a few minutes, then make into rolls.
Let rise and bake in 350° oven.

title: butterfly lamb with rosemary
directions: Place the lamb in a shallow pan.
Combine the oil, lemon juice, rosemary, pepper and bay leaf.
Blend well and rub the mixture all over the lamb.
Cover and let stand for 2 hours or longer, unrefrigerated but in a cool place.
Turn the meat occasionally.

title: baked chicken breasts with cheese
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish. Cover with cheese.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over cheese. Sprinkle croutons on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: favorite honey bars
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and honey until light and fluffy.
Add egg and blend.
Mix together dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Spread into 10 1/2 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: new york jewish penicillin
directions: Place all of above ingredients, except dill and noodles, in large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 1/2 hours, skimming top for sediment.
Remove all of ingredients from soup. Return some chicken pieces and carrot pieces to soup.
Skim fat off top.
Serve with fresh dill and freshly boiled noodles.

title: potato soup plus
directions: Put potatoes, carrots and onions in a big pot with just enough water to cover.
Boil until tender.
Do not drain! Mash.
Stir in browned sausage, butter, cheese and spices.
Simmer a few minutes, until cheese melts and flavors blend.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place first three ingredients in a plastic bag and shake.
Put in Bundt pan, sprayed with Pam.
Melt butter.
Add remaining sugar and cinnamon to melted butter. Pour over mixture in Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out right away.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Put cabbage leaves in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Put 2 to 4 tablespoons meat on cabbage leaf.
Roll cabbage leaf and place in kettle.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer until tender.
It takes about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: frank's famous spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Chop tomatoes, onion, pepperoni, cheese and olives.
Mix all ingredients with the dressing.
Chill.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Stir in okra.
Pour oil to depth of 2-inches into frying pan or deep fat fryer at 350°.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil and cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 of broth to meat. Cook spaghetti noodles.
Add soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix and add spaghetti.
Place grated cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: lois' jello
directions: Prepare lemon Jell-O with a little less water so that it is firm.
Let partially set.
Add pineapple, sour cream, Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into mold and let set.

title: melon pops
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into 8 (5 ounce) paper cups.
Cover each cup with foil.
Make a small hole in the foil with a knife.
Insert a wooden stick into cup through the hole.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.

title: double cheese meat roll
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese and tomato sauce in a small bowl along with basil and oregano.
Set aside.

title: aunt pam's best blueberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Press into greased oblong baking dish along bottom and up sides.
Bake until golden brown at 350 degrees.
Set aside to cool.
Cream together sugar, cream cheese and cool whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Spread blueberry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave (read package directions).
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour into aluminum foil lined cookie sheets to 1/4-inch thickness.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle over the semi-cooled almond bark.
Cut through with knife to give swirled look.
Cut into pieces.

title: macaroni and ground beef
directions: Fry ground beef with onion.
Cook macaroni in boiling salted water.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Season to taste and let simmer about 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal rum-raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Soak raisins in rum. (The raisins can be soaked in apple juice instead of rum.) Beat together the butter and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well. Stir in oats and raisins and mix well (I like to add walnuts or pecans here). Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or longer for more crispy cookies. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack. Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: diet salad
directions: Boil pineapple and jello for 3 minutes.
Cool; whip the Dream Whip.
Mix Dream Whip and cottage cheese into jello.
Chill until firm.

title: lentil side dish
directions: Saute onion and fennel in olive oil until soft. Add lentils and broth and bring to boil; lower heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Add the tomatoes, Italian seasonings, oregano, garlic, bay leaf and salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in the parsley flakes and couscous (optional); cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir and serve.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pie filling and vanilla wafers).
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake liner.
Fill 2/3 with cream cheese mixture.
To with pie filling.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spicy chili with sour cream dumplings
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic in 4-quart Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except dumplings.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the soups, sour cream, mayo and garlic powder until well blended to make the sauce.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer half the noodles, half the chicken, half the sauce and half the cheese.
Repeat the layers and bake for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together the eggs, oil and vanilla until frothy.
Stir in the sugar.
Sift together and stir in the dry ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy elegant chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in amounts needed.
Add mayonnaise to taste.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: pimiento cheese dip
directions: Whisk together the first 3 ingredients and cook until thick. Cool.
Mix well with remaining ingredients and serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour in lightly greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until done at 425°.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak squash, onions and green peppers in salt water for 1 hour; drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and pimento; mix well.
Add squash, onions and peppers to sugar mixture.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Put in hot canning jars; seal while hot.
Makes 6 pints.

title: custard sauce
directions: Scald the milk in a double boiler.
Beat the egg yolks slightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Add the milk, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Return to the double boiler and cook over hot, not boiling water, until mixture coats spoon, stirring constantly.
Remove at once.
Cool and add vanilla.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 9 minutes.
Mix mayonnaise, cottage cheese, cream cheese and dressing mix together.
Add a little milk, if too thick.
Spread on cooled rolls and top with 2 cups chopped vegetables (your choice).
Cauliflower, broccoli, radishes and carrots work well. Add grated cheese on top.

title: rye bread pizzas
directions: Brown and drain meats.
Melt cheeses and mix together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread over mini rye bread.
Heat and serve.

title: morgan's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Gradually add and beat until creamy the sugars. Beat in the egg and vanilla. Stir in the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Add the chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop the batter from a teaspoon, well apart, on cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: fried rice(lo-cal)
directions: Brown turkey, onion and pepper until tender.
Add rice and stir-fry.
Top with scrambled egg.
Serves 3.

title: aunt irene's courtland stew
directions: Boil hen in small amount of salted water.
Remove meat from bone and return to stock.
Add whole potatoes and when done, remove and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except corn, at the same time as potatoes.
Add corn after stew is nearly done. Cooking time is about 5 hours.
Can be modified for crock-pot.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add cooking oil.
Add 1 cup cool water.
Dissolve yeast in above mixture.
Add the sugar and salt.
Sift in 6 to 7 cups flour, or enough flour until dough is not sticky.
Let raise to double in size.
Work down and make into rolls.
Let raise again.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: sauerkraut beef casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, place the sauerkraut, rice and beef in order given.
Over the top, pour undiluted tomato soup and undiluted chicken noodle soup.
DO NOT STIR.
Leave in layers. Sprinkle with wheat germ or crushed cornflakes (optional).
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma's black walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt three times; set aside. Blend sugar, margarine and Crisco together.
Add eggs individually and beat with each one.
Beat until fluffy.
Put in flour mixture and milk a little at a time and blend.
Add lemon and vanilla. Flour walnuts to keep from sinking.
Stir in walnuts with spoon. Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pie(sophia wood)
directions: Bake pastry shell according to package directions. Cream butter until soft. Gradually blend in sugar, then add flour.

title: fudge
directions: Cook the sugar, butter, margarine and evaporated milk as fast as it will go stirring all the time (it should cook in five minutes).
Use the cup of cold water to drop a bit in it and when it forms as it goes down and the tail gets hard, you are ready to add the last three items.
First add the marshmallow cream.
(It comes out of the jar easier if you soak the jar in hot water prior to use.)
Add the seven squares of chocolate.
Once it melts real good, add pecans.
Beat until it gets a glossy look.
Butter your pan and then pour fudge into pan and let set.

title: mashed potatoes(to freeze)
directions: Mix ingredients and mash or whip until fluffy.
Add little milk if necessary.
Put in containers suitable for self or family. Freeze.
When ready to use, drizzle butter over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour to heat through good at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread with green onions and cheese
directions: In the large bowl of the electric mixer, beat together first 5 ingredients until butter is the size of small peas.
Beat in the next 4 ingredients until blended.
Beat milk and egg, then add to the bowl, stirring until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into oiled 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until top is golden brown and a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
(If top is browning too quickly, then tent loosely with foil.)
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan and continue cooling on a rack. Yields one loaf.

title: shrimp olive(microwave)
directions: Place butter, onion and garlic in large glass dish; microwave for 2 minutes.
Then add shrimp, parsley, paprika, Tabasco and cayenne pepper.
Cook an additional 7 minutes, stirring twice. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Serve over cooked egg noodles tossed with butter and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Pound steak to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in 1/2-inch wide strips across grain of meat.
Sprinkle with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Using a large skillet, brown meat in margarine.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring until clear and thickened for about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve over the hot rice.
Serves 4 nicely.
Good and it's quick!

title: beef bacon bit cornbread
directions: Fry bacon in frying pan and break into very small pieces. Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; mix thoroughly.
Add milk, stirring slowly.
Add eggs and blend well.
Melt butter in the baking pan and pour into cornmeal batter and mix well.
Add the bacon pieces and stir very well.
Pour the batter mix into the baking pan and cook for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix together and dissolve in hot water the raspberry jello and sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour into large container and freeze.
When ready to serve, cut frozen mixture into pieces and put into punch bowl. Pour chilled Sprite or ginger ale over mixture and serve.

title: mom's coffee cake
directions: Grease an 8-inch pan with butter.
Mix oil with egg and milk. Mix dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture.
Pour batter into pan. Stir just barely to smooth out lumps.
Sprinkle 4 tablespoons sugar mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top of batter. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: puddin's egg kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar gradually.
Beat until real stiff.
Add vanilla.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheets covered in brown paper.
Bake in preheated oven of 325° for 5 minutes.
Then turn oven off.
Wait until oven is cool, then remove and enjoy.

title: easy mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Grease muffin pans.
Pour into muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This recipe makes 6 muffins.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over 4 boneless chicken breasts and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In skillet, brown sausage; drain well.
Add all ingredients to a crock-pot and stir well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 12 hours.
Taste for seasoning.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: foundation yellow cake
directions: Cream the butter or shortening thoroughly in a deep bowl. (Have it soft before you start.)

Add sugar gradually, beating until the mixture is fluffy and light like whipped cream. Add eggs, beaten until light. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with liquid, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Beat thoroughly and add flavoring.
Bake in layers or flat loaf pan in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 large squares or 3 layers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add milk and cream.
Blend in beaten egg yolk, sugar and flour.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: sauteed zucchini-carrots
directions: Saute carrots in oleo on medium heat.
Heat 4 minutes.
Add onions.
Cook 1 minute.
Add zucchini, salt, pepper and basil. Cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Heat oven to 300. In a 3 quart casserole or Dutch oven, brown beef cubes in oil. Stir in flour, salt, and pepper. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover and bake at 300 for 2 to 3 hours, stirring every hour. Serve over cooked noodles OR rice.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie filling). Pour 2/3 of batter into greased jelly roll pan. Spread on pie filling. Drop rest of batter by spoonfuls on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into one or two balls. Sprinkle each ball with paprika.
Chill.

title: hamburger potato hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger in the shortening. Add the onion and celery.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place hamburger in buttered casserole. Top with the tomato soup.
Add layers of potatoes and top with the cream of mushroom soup. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: delicious fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour into a one-gallon freezer and freeze.
Let ripen at least one hour.

title: swedish ginger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
With electric mixer, cream together oil and sugar.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Shape dough into walnut-size balls, roll in sugar and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until cookies are golden brown and cracked on top.
Let cool on wire racks.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package. Cool. Mix together sour cream, 2 packages of coconut and sugar. Frost cake. Add remaining coconut to top of cake. Refrigerate.

title: swiss ham ring-around
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
In a large mixing bowl, combine parsley, onion, mustard, margarine and lemon juice; blend well.
Add cheese, broccoli and ham; mix lightly. Set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
On greased cookie sheet, arrange triangles with points toward the outside in a circle with bases overlapping.
The center opening should be about 3 inches in diameter.
Spoon ham filling in a ring evenly over bases of triangles.
(Some filling may fall onto cookie sheet.) Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under bases of triangles at center of circle.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix cereal, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Add beaten eggs, shortening and milk to flour mixture.
Mix well. Put into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Mix will hold for 6 weeks if covered and kept in refrigerator.

title: pineapple-zucchini cake
directions: In bowl, blend eggs and sugar. Add Crisco oil and vanilla. Blend well.
Add baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix well.
Add flour alternately with zucchini and blend.
Then add pineapple, currants and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour batter in two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool 10 minutes and turn out on cooling racks.

title: barbara's apple spice
directions: Mix sugar, oil, coffee, eggs and applesauce.
Add dry ingredients and mix all together.
Stir in diced apples.
Pour onto cookie sheet (type used in Food Services).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle in graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle in chocolate chips.
Sprinkle in coconut. Sprinkle in chopped pecans.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: mother's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar with shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°; watch closely.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: white potato pie
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes in clear water until done. Drain well.
Put in mixing bowl and combine with all other ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased bread pans at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients
well and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: party punch
directions: Pour chilled juice and ginger ale into punch bowl and mix. Top with scoops of sherbet.
Makes 25 servings.

title: sugar pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Slowly add milk and cream to make a smooth mixture.
Cook until bubbly and thickened (I put in microwave 6 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally). Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix well. Stir and bring to a boil until like syrup. Pour over ham last 15 minutes of baking.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion and peppers until tender-crisp.
Drain peach liquid into skillet with vegetables.
Add vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Return chicken to skillet.
Simmer 1 hour.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to chicken and vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Add peach halves. Heat through.

title: super fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks. Put the pineapple juice in a saucepan with sugar, cornstarch, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook until thickened.
Set aside to cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of oil.
Lift out and pour off grease.
Spread rice over bottom of skillet.
Add water; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Put pork chops back in skillet on the rice and sprinkle with remaining teaspoon of salt.
Add onions, chopped tomatoes with juice and drained corn.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bring to boil.
Turn down low.
Cover and simmer 25 to 35 minutes.
Watch and add more water should it cook dry or if rice should not be tender.

title: banana cream drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine butter and cream cheese and beat until creamy.

Add cake mix and eggs. Beat until smooth. Stir in white chocolate chips and pecans. Drop from spoon onto ungreased baking sheet, spacing cookies about 2 inches apart. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from cookie sheet and place on rack to cool. Makes about 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: beef stroganoff(from overrock inn)
directions: Brown tenderloin tips.
Brown flour in butter or margarine. Add wine and vinegar to meat juices from browning meat.
Make a brown sauce using browned flour.
Put the tips in the sauce; add seasonings and mushrooms.
Remove from heat and add sour cream. Serve on noodles or toast points.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add Ro-Tel, beans and soups.
Stir and cook until well heated.
Line an 8 1/2 x 12-inch pan or baking dish with Fritos.
Pour mixture on top of Fritos. Cover with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: holiday ham and cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, deviled ham, scallions and chilies.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into a ball. Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill.
Remove from refrigerator to soften slightly before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Makes one 2 cup cheese ball.

title: red dressing
directions: Mix together and keep refrigerated for tossed salads.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder and baking soda together.
In large bowl mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add milk to dry ingredients.
Mix 2 minutes.
Add coffee.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: larry's country cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Return to skillet.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce, cooked rice and brown sugar.
Simmer 1 minute.
Pour ingredients into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Pour prepared cornbread mixture on top of cheese.
Bake as directed per cornbread directions.
Serve with salad.

title: crab dip
directions: Cut Seablend up.
Stir in other ingredients (except almonds) until creamy.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: thai lemon grass soup
