directions: Heat chicken broth in a pot.
Cut lemon grass into 1-inch lengths.
Add lime leaves, lemon grass, galangal and chicken to the broth.
Heat until chicken is cooked through, then add lime juice, fish sauce, chilies and mushrooms.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Garnish with cilantro and serve.

title: chinese noodle cookies - no bake!
directions: In heavy saucepan, slowly melt all chips; add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add noodles; stir well.
Cool slightly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to harden.
They may be put in refrigerator overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cube and boil zucchini 6 minutes and drain.
Mix sour cream, soup and onion.
Pour over squash and mix together.
Melt oleo and add to Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Put half of dressing in baking dish.
Add zucchini, then put the rest of the dressing on top. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: jello-cottage cheese salad
directions: Stir dry orange jello into cottage cheese; mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip and then add mandarin oranges.
If desired, you may use eight of the orange slices to decorate the top of the salad.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, Crisco, salt and butter.
Set aside to cool.
After cool, dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Combine milk mixture and yeast mixture.
Add eggs; stir in flour.
Dough will be soft and slightly sticky.
Knead dough on floured surface for 10 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Punch down; let rise to double again.
Divide into 4 pieces.
Roll into jelly roll; spread melted butter on dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Roll into jelly roll; slice.
Let rise and bake at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and stir in cream of mushroom soup until completely mixed.
Stir in 3/4 can of fried onion rings and pour remaining on top of mixture.
Bake in a covered dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: On a well greased 15-inch pizza pan, press out cookie dough into a 14-inch circle.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Combine cream cheese, peanut butter, and sugar.
Spread this mixture evenly over cooled cookie.
Arrange apple slices over this mixture.
Uniformly sprinkle on chopped peanuts and drizzle with caramel topping.
Slice and serve with vanilla ice cream or cool whip.

title: cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick butter in square baking pan.
Pour batter over butter.
Pour fruit on top of batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix ingredients (except chocolate) and refrigerate.
Roll in small balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper or cookie sheet until dry.
Store in refrigerator.
These are great for Christmas holidays.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve 1 package gelatin with 1 cup boiling water.
Add defrosted strawberries.
Let cool.
Whip topping, following directions on box and fold into strawberry mixture.
Cut up cake into small squares.
Lightly oil a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour 1/4 of whipped mixture into pan.
Place pieces of cake on top, then cover with remainder of whipped mixture.
Refrigerate.
Dissolve other package of gelatin according to package directions.
Let cool until it is syrupy.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice in
a
saucepan.	Mix
in
jello. Put in marshmallows and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt.	Remove	from
heat and cool, then add nuts, pineapple, Cool
Whip
and	cottage cheese.
Pour in mold and let jell.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together flour and baking soda.
Blend in sugar mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar and milk.
Boil for 2 minutes; take off stove.
Add oats, cocoa and vanilla.
Drop onto wax paper with spoon.
Let set up.

title: pork chop dinner electric skillet
directions: Brown pork chops with onions, add seasoning and water.
Add potatoes and carrots (thin sliced) and celery (thick).
Simmer until done.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; mix well. Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Add oats; mix well.
Quickly drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: big bubbles
directions: Mix ingredients gently in bucket.
Let settle for 3 to 4 hours.
Makes super big bubbles.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer the 6 ingredients in the order given above. Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: turtle bread
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Heat water, milk and margarine to about 130°.
Stir in yeast mixture, egg and enough remaining dough to make flour easy to handle.
Sprinkle flour on wax paper and knead dough until elastic and smooth.
Cover for 10 minutes.

title: easy, crusty cut outs
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Let crust soften to room temperature.
Sprinkle a little flour on kitchen counter and place crust on top.
Using whatever cookie cutters you like, cut out as many shapes as you can.
You will need a rolling pin to re-roll extra pastry.
Sprinkle with cinnamon & sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes & cool on paper towels.

title: camp taters
directions: Put oil into a heavy skillet over medium heat; dump vegetables in.
Stir; cover tightly and simmer until tender.
Take lid off and evaporate liquid.
Cook and toss until bottom is lightly browned and crusty.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef and onion in 10-inch pan.
Drain beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-covered easter eggs
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar, salt and water, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring until mixture reaches firm ball stage (248° on candy thermometer).
Slowly pour half of sugar mixture over beaten egg whites, beating constantly with electric mixer.
Cook remaining half of sugar mixture over medium heat to hard ball stage (260° on candy thermometer).
Pour mixture slowly over egg white mixture; beat until mixture holds its shape and mixer cannot beat any more. Beat with wooden spoon until mixture is no longer glossy.
Stir in pecans and cherries.
Shape mixture into 2-inch eggs or 2 large eggs.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin in a saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Dip each egg into chocolate; cool on waxed paper.
Reheat chocolate if it thickens.
Decorate as desired with decorator icing.
Yield:
About 30 (2-inch) eggs or 2 (1 1/4 to 1 1/2 pound) eggs.

title: gak (silly putty)
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a bowl.
Mix 1/2 cup water and Borax in a styrofoam cup.
Stir mixtures together.
(Fast - hands on.)

title: cheese-shrimp fondue
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Remove crust from bread; cut slices into cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and shrimp.
Pour into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch oblong baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered 1 hour or until center is set.
Serve immediately.

title: spoon bread(corn)
directions: Mix margarine, egg and sour cream.
Add 2 cans of corn, then add muffin mix.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash the shrimp with a fork and combine with all ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: quick breakfast sweet rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Remove rolls from package, leaving in rectangular shape.
Seal perforations.
Spread pecan mixture over dough.
Starting with long side, roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Pinch seam to seal (do not seal ends).
Cut roll into 12 slices.
Place in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, water, cornstarch and Jell-O to boil until glossy, about 2 minutes.
Cool.
Bake pie shell.
Cool.
Slice strawberries to top of pie shell.
Pour Jell-O mixture over strawberries.
Chill until mixture sets.
Top with Cool Whip or other toppings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine chopped vegetables and sauerkraut. Mix vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour dressing over salad and mix. Let set overnight.

title: cherwine punch
directions: Have pineapple juice real cold.
Add at serving time, then add Cherwine.
Makes about 1 gallon.
Serve over crushed ice or make ring mold of 1 can of red Hi-C punch.
The Cherwine and pineapple don't freeze well.
The good part about this punch is you mix it as needed without leftovers.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in frypan over medium heat; add meat and brown.
Add onions and green peppers.
Mix salt, pepper and cornstarch; add broth and soy sauce.
Pour over meat and bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: layered salad
directions: In a 4-quart bowl layer each ingredient in the following order:
Lettuce, onion, celery, drained water chestnuts, thawed peas, mushrooms, 2 cups mayonnaise (spread), sugar, cheese, seasoned salt, table salt, egg and bacon.

title: zucchini or summer squash casserole
directions: Cut unpared zucchini/squash into bite size pieces.
Mix ingredients with 1/2 of the dressing mix.
Put in casserole and top with balance of dressing.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes at 350°.

title: date cake
directions: Mix and let stand water, chopped dates and soda.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and then add date mixture.
Bake at 350°.

title: spiders
directions: Melt morsels in microwave or double boiler.
Add peanuts and noodles to melted morsels.
Using teaspoon, drop small amount onto wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rice
directions: Cover bottom of hot ovenproof pan with butter, swish to cover bottom.
Mix rice with mandarin peel, put in pan and stir to coat rice with butter.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stir constantly.
Pour chicken stock over rice, add saffron and bay leaf, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in 450° oven for 20 minutes.
When rice is cooked, all liquid absorbed, remove bay leaf.
Add almonds and mandarin segments. Serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix well the 1 cup flour, softened butter and powdered sugar and pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Put buttermilk, butter, corn syrup, baking soda and sugar into a large 6 to 8-quart pot.
Place on low heat, stirring until sugar is melted.
Cook to 236° on candy thermometer or until soft ball forms when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until mixture becomes thick and loses it's gloss.
Pour into buttered 12 x 14-inch pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Puree the tomatoes and sugar.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Set aside and skim.
Add jello.
Return to stove and cook until jello is dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal with paraffin.

title: cookie ice cream rounds
directions: Bake cookies like the tube says.
Cool.
Put ice cream between 2 cookies and press together.
Wrap in foil and freeze.

title: melrose hare's coconut pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, 1/2 cup milk, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
In 2-quart saucepan, heat 1 1/2 cups milk to scalding.
Add egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until filling is thick and boils.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour into pie crust.
Cover with egg white meringue and sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: spinach or broccoli souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a lightly greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Prepare tube pan with butter and coat with sugar.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and beat. Dredge berries in remaining flour; gently add to mixture.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yellow layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round or two 9-inch square cake pans.

title: heath bar delight
directions: Divide prepared cake in half and break the half into bite size pieces.
Place in a trifle or fancy glass bowl.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sauce or liqueur onto the cake pieces.
Pour on 1/2 of the prepared pudding and spread over cake.
Spoon on 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on 1/2 crushed Heath bars.
Repeat layers, beginning with the other half of the cake.
Top with remaining crumbled Heath bar.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest.
Heat at 350° (on medium high in stove) until bubbly.
Let stand for 2 days. Heat and eat!
Serves 6.

title: dough for 12-inch pizza
directions: Mix the yeast, salt and oil with the water.
Add this mixture to flour and mix well.
Cover dough and place in a warm place for 1 hour.
When dough is doubled in size, knead the dough briefly. Dough may then be rolled out or patted into a 12-inch pizza pan that has been greased.
Add desired toppings and bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Shape into small balls and press flat each way with fork.
Dip fork in flour.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand and chill overnight.

title: spaghetti pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook beef and onion in large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is brown, stirring to separate meat.
Drain meat of fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; mix well.

title: family chicken 'n chili casserole
directions: Mix together the soups, broth, chili, mushrooms and chicken. Lightly fry tortillas in oil; drain.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half of the tortillas.
Add half of the chicken-soup mixture, half of the onions and half of the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook Knox soup mix as directed in a large saucepan.
Add frozen broccoli cuts.
Mix in Campbell's soup and 1 can of milk. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cheese and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring squash, onions, butter, salt and pepper to a boil. Cook for approximately 25 minutes. Add cheese, eggs, milk and 2 slices of toast (cut into small pieces). Mix well. Put mixed ingredients into buttered medium-sized baking dish and top with remaining bread. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: You will also need rock salt, ice and ice cream maker.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to boil the margarine, water and cocoa, stirring to prevent lumps.
Cool a little.
Add flour, sugar, salt and baking soda which have been sifted into large bowl.
In small bowl, beat eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and egg mixture to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured sheet cake pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: ham on pineapple
directions: Mix ham with mayonnaise and mustard.
Shape into patties. Place on pineapple slices.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa and cool.
Blend sugar and eggs, add flour and pecans.
Add cooled mixture and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 375° (350° for glass) until cake tests done, between 25 to 30 minutes.
While still hot, spread marshmallow cream on cake.
Spread icing over marshmallow cream while still warm. Should be baked at least 1 day before needed.
Very rich!

title: butternut chewies
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and margarine until creamy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts.
(Mixture will be stiff.)
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lemon lush
directions: For the crust layer, cut butter into flour until well blended. Add walnuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Thinly slice potatoes to measure 6 cups.
Place half of the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add half the onion.
Sift half the flour and add to ham and vegetables in casserole; sprinkle with half the salt and pepper.
Repeat layers. Pour milk over all.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and continue baking 15 to 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except corn flakes and butter) well and place in greased casserole.
Top with crushed flakes and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: In saucepan, mix soup
and milk; heat on medium and add cheese.
Cook chicken and cut up.
Cook noodles and drain.
Steam or boil broccoli until bright green and fork-tender.
Stir soup mixture until cheese is melted.
Then combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Lightly grease casserole dish and spread mixture in evenly.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Put in casserole with lid. Make 1 day ahead and refrigerate. Bake when ready to use at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company shrimp casserole
directions: Saute celery, pepper, onions and shrimp (shrimp may be cut up in smaller pieces).
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Bake, covered, in casserole, at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover top with grated cheese.

title: basil grilled chicken(serving size:  4)
directions: Press pepper into meaty sides of chicken breast halves. Combine melted butter and chopped basil; stir well.
Brush chicken lightly with melted butter mixture.
Combine softened butter, basil, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Beat at low speed of an electric mixer until mixture is well blended and smooth.
Transfer to a small serving bowl; set aside. Grill chicken over medium coals, 8 to 10 minutes on each side, basting frequently with remaining melted butter mixture.
Serve grilled chicken with basil-butter mixture.
Garnish with fresh basil sprigs, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and chill at least 1 hour.
Put fresh fruit around.

title: minute-boil fudge frosting
directions: Bring slowly to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil briskly 1 minute (1 1/2 minutes on a rainy day).
Cool and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until thick.
A rotary beater may be used.
Frost the cake before the frosting becomes too thick.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Whip with mixer until thoroughly blended.

title: pita(greek spinach pie)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Put butter in saucepan; melt.
Saute onion and garlic. Sprinkle flour in; add milk, tomatoes, corn, salmon and seasoning. Simmer on low for 5 to 10 minutes.
Delicious with Aunt Monnie's home canned salmon.

title: jimmy's potatoes
directions: *Tabasco sauce may be added for a variation.

title: holy mole sauce
directions: Grind the peppers, anise seed, sesame seed, garlic, almonds, tortillas and tomatoes.
Mix into a paste and add all the spices, including the chocolate.
Place the oil in a frying pan and add the mixture to it.
Fry for several minutes, then add the stock and simmer until quite thick.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients and mix; do not salt chicken before fixing it.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in eggs and grated cheese. Place half in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Add rest of spaghetti.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cover with sauce at the table.

title: garden bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans.
Place in a large bowl.
Add green pepper, celery, pimento and onions; set aside.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil in a heavy saucepan; boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; immediately pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, cake flour, salt and baking powder.
Add chocolate syrup and vanilla last.
Mix and bake 30 to 35 minutes in 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: t~e~g's easy pork chop meal
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and drain grease. Using oven dish, layer pork chops, mushrooms and onion. Top with Minute rice. Combine soup and water; pour over mixture. Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken consomme with avocado
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the chicken broth; do not let it boil.
Place slices of avocado in the bottom of each soup plate. Top with 2 slices of lemon.
Pour the chicken broth over the avocado and lemon.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons of sherry to each bowl. Sprinkle chopped parsley on top.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef-a-ronie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato juice, sugar, salt, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and macaroni.
Slowly cook for 30 minutes.

title: quick mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pour into greased (or spray with Pam) 8-inch iron skillet.
Bake approximately 15 minutes until done. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caesar salad
directions: Marinate garlic in olive oil for 30 minutes.
Hard-cook eggs for 7 minutes; cool and remove shell.
Remove garlic from the olive oil and set aside.
Using 2 tablespoons of the olive oil, brown bread cubes in large skillet over medium heat.
Set aside. Put all remaining ingredients (olive oil, garlic, egg, lemon juice, salt, pepper, anchovies and cheese), except lettuce, in food processor or blender and mix well.
Put lettuce that has been washed, dried and torn into bite sized pieces, in a large bowl. Add mixture from blender and toss.
Add bread cubes and toss again.

title: apple crisp (with instant pudding mix)
directions: Mix milk with 1/4 cup pudding mix and pour over apple slices in 8 x 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla; blend.
Add flour which has been sifted with the baking powder and cinnamon, then add rest of pudding mix and nuts.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Delicious served with vanilla ice cream.

title: rice confetti salad
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients together thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with cherry tomatoes.

title: peach custard
directions: Slice peaches into pie shell.
Stir other ingredients until pasty.
Cook until thick.
Pour over peaches.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix Duncan Hines cake and cook as directed.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and water (add enough to make 1 1/2 cups) and coconut. Punch holes in cake when done and pour over warm cake.
Let cool. Ice.

title: school rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine ingredients.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Grease pans.
Add plain flour, enough to make medium stiff.
Pour on floured surface.
Knead until firm.
Make small rolls and place butter on top.
Let roll rise until double. Bake until brown.
Serving around 40.

title: sopa de tortilla(tortilla soup)
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil. Add beef and chicken broths, tomato juice, cumin, chili powder, jalapeno pepper, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Cut corn tortillas into narrow strips.
Heat oil in skillet and fry tortillas until crisp. Drain on paper towels.
Add chicken and tomato to soup; cook 5 minutes.
Place 2 to 3 tortilla strips in each soup bowl. Pour soup into bowls and garnish with avocado slices and 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: black bean turkey chili
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, heat oil over low heat. Saute the onions and red pepper for about 10 minutes or until tender but not browned. Add the sausage and turkey and brown over medium heat. Drain any excess fat from pan. Add the garlic, chiles, pepper, salt, chili powder, oregano, basil and tomato paste. Stir in the tomatoes, beer and beans. Simmer over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes. Taste to adjust seasonings. Stir in cilantro leaves before serving. May be made ahead and reheated. Serves 8 to 10.

title: deep fried calamari
directions: Wash and dry calamari as best as possible to avoid splattering. Heat oil until it sizzles when you put in a piece of calamari (test it first).
Dredge calamari lightly in flour and deep fry until golden brown.
Serve hot with lemon juice, tartar sauce, cocktail sauce or hot sauce.

title: german chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine kidney beans, cabbage, tomatoes, bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce in large pan. Pour 2-quarts water over mixture and add ground beef.
Cook approximately 2 hours or until cabbage is tender.

title: brown sugar meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 5 x 9 inch loaf pan. Press the brown sugar in the bottom of the prepared loaf pan and spread the ketchup over the sugar.
In a mixing bowl, mix thoroughly all remaining ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Place on top of the ketchup.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour or until juices are clear.

title: cornbread salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together pepper, tomatoes, onion, bacon, eggs, and cornbread.
Add enough mayonnaise to make mixture moist (mixture should stick together).
Allow to stand overnight in refrigerator in covered dish.

title: aunt bet's fantastic potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Slice oleo over potatoes. Sprinkle Accent over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing mix and spread over cooked potatoes. Spread cheese over this and cook at 350° until sour cream is hot (somewhere around 5 to 10 minutes).

title: fireside stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil at medium heat.
Drain fat.
Drain and reserve liquid from potatoes, carrots and beans.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Add meat.
Stir in tomato sauce and thyme.
Cover and simmer 1 3/4 hours.
Add vegetables. Simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: scottish oat scones
directions: Add margarine, milk and eggs to combined dry ingredients; mix until just moist.
Add raisins.
Shape dough to form ball; pat out on floured surface to form 8-inch circle.
Cut into 12 wedges. Bake on greased cookie sheet in preheated 425° oven for 12 minutes, or until light golden brown.

title: basic molasses cake
directions: Cream butter, slowly add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk beginning and ending with flour.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Squeeze water from kraut.
Add carrot and relish.
Boil oil, vinegar and sugar.
Cool and mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all well and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Bake in 1-quart casserole dish for 1/2 hour.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Butter 8 x 8-inch pan. Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add marshmallows.
Stir in until well blended.
Remove from stove and stir in nuts.
Pat down in buttered square pan.
When cool, but not set, cut into squares or just break apart.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 40 minutes in 325° oven until golden brown. Leave cake in pan and pour frosting on top while still hot.

title: ruby nell's own soup (squash)
directions: Cook until tender; add 2 tablespoons margarine just before done.
Add:

title: whipped jello
directions: Make jello per directions.
Set until thickened.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: our favorite salad
directions: Mix vegetables.
Break Feta over salad, then cover to preference with dressing.
Serves 4.

title: almond rolls
directions: In large skillet, combine all ingredients except confectioners sugar; heat, stirring,
over low heat until butter is melted and mixture is mushy.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart on greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake 1 sheet at a time in 350° oven for 5 or 6 minutes, until golden brown; then remove, one at a time, from cookie sheet.
Quickly roll up around handle of a wooden spoon and cool.
To serve, dust with sifted confectioners sugar and fill with whipped cream from a pastry tube.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, pineapple and onion.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake in cold oven at 325° until it springs back when touched, about 1 hour.

title: marietta's vegetable beef soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot and cook until done.

title: pumpkin soup with lentils(62 calories per cup; 2 grams fat)
directions: In an iron Dutch oven, melt the butter and stir in the flour. Carefully add the water, stirring to keep consistency smooth.
Add chopped onion, pumpkin and bouillon cubes, lentils and spices and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and puree.

title: tuna salad - disney world
directions: Put tunas and celery in a strainer; drain overnight in the refrigerator.
Chop tuna very fine.
Mix tuna and celery with remaining ingredients until well blended.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Yield:
4 to 5 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Empty beans into colander and pour hot water over them to remove sauce.
Drain and chill.
Combine with eggs, celery, onion, pickles and salt with salad dressing thinned with catsup.
Serve in lettuce cups and garnish with onion rings or parsley.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain all juice from fruits and place in large mixing bowl. Sprinkle vanilla pudding and mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix in coconut.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: linguine a la anne
directions: Cook linguine; drain and return to pot.
While linguine cooks, melt margarine in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour and salt, adding evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add liquid from mushrooms, water and bouillon cube.
Cook
over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly and slightly thickened.
Add 2 cups sauce and mushrooms to linguine and toss until well mixed.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, pressing it up the sides and leave a slight hollow in center of dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Before serving, sprinkle croutons around edge of casserole.

title: grandma's chicken and rice
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and can of water with bouillon cube and pour over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip(in honor of "dan patch")
directions: Combine all ingredients except spinach.
Squeeze spinach and stir in a little at a time.
Best when made the night before.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Preheat oven to broil or 425°.
Spray pan with vegetable spray. Then put the chicken in the pan and sprinkle the lemon pepper on it.
Add more pepper, if desired.
Put the chicken in the oven on broil for 8 to 10 minutes or 10 to 12 minutes at 425° for more moistness.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Put peanuts into blender or food processor.
Gradually add 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil, blending until texture is thick and creamy.
Keep homemade peanut butter refrigerated.
If oil separates, stir back in with spoon.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put into two loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix together; add water to make 2 gallons.
Put in freezer for 8 hours.
Stir every hour, for slushy effect while in the freezer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and add taco seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Layer ingredients in this order in round dish, using 1/4 amount each time:
tortilla, refried beans, beef mixture, salsa, tomatoes, sour cream and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy; set aside.
Beat margarine with chocolate.
Add to egg mixture and beat well. Add vanilla and beat until well blended.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mustard cheese dip
directions: Combine and blend all ingredients.
Serve with crackers. Yield: one cup.

title: french silk chocolate
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add cooled, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix tuna, bread crumbs, 1 can cream of celery soup, onion and eggs well.
Pack lightly into loaf pan and bake 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft, 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: better than toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, eggs, sugars and vanilla until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in oven at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: sesame strips
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Take the frozen bread from the freezer and spread on mixture.
Cut each slice of frozen bread into 4 to 6 strips.
Place on tinfoil lined cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Store in airtight container.
They last a long time.

title: mom's (doris') taco chicken
directions: Combine flour and taco seasoning. Roll or shake chicken in mixture. Melt butter in pan. Roll chicken in melted butter, then roll in corn chips and return to pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy, add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool one minute on cookie sheet, remove to wire racks.

title: carrot ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients;
chill for 1 hour and serve in lettuce cup.

title: pop-up cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking
pan.
Pour
in
crust.
Add warmed fruit. Bake until brown at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: easy rice dish
directions: Mix; bake in casserole dish at 350° until done.

title: cornish game hens and rice
directions: Spread rice in a 3-quart shallow baking dish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden. Combine salad dressing and mix with 2 1/2-cups boiling water and chicken soup, then stir into rice. Cut game hens in half lengthwise; season, if you wish, with salt and pepper. Place game hens, cut side down, on top of rice. Cover dish tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover; bake 30 minutes longer or until rice and hens are tender.

title: turtle candy
directions: Put all of syrup, sugar and 1/2 of cream in pan; bring to a boil.
Stir mixture constantly.
Add rest of cream and oleo slowly so mixture does not stop boiling.
Boil to soft ball on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla and pour over pecans.
Have pecans ready single layer on pan.

title: angel food refrigerator cake
directions: Melt together the chocolate chips and 1 1/2 tablespoons cool water.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
When cool, fold in beaten egg whites and fold in the preceding.
Add the whipped cream.
Put a layer of cake, broken into bite size pieces, into a dish.
Add 1/2 of sauce.
Add another layer of cake; finish with sauce.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill several hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in four layers.
(You can make 2 layers and split.)
While cake is baking, prepare filling.
Mix softened cream cheese with sugar, then blend in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture and pie filling between each layer including top of cake.

title: delicious bean pot recipe
directions: Combine beans, which have not been drained, with all ingredients in al large casserole.
Bake uncovered in a 300° oven for at least 2 hours (longer is O.K.).
Some liquid cooks away, but do not let them get dry.
After baking, remove bay leaf.

title: chicken corn noodle soup
directions: Slice cucumber and onion to fill approximately a 2-quart bowl. Mix the following dressing and pour over cucumber and onion.

title: steak or chicken stir-fry
directions: Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Melt butter in small cast-iron skillet.
Stir together the flour, corn meal, egg and buttermilk and add butter.
Leave small amount of butter in bottom and along sides of skillet.
Pour mixture into heated skillet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature, then grate.
In a mixing bowl, combine grated cheese, diced pimentos (do not drain), salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate.
Use as desired.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Cook onions and bell pepper with thyme in bacon drippings until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chick 'n bean soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add broth, tomatoes, carrots and picante sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Combine butter, sour cream and half and half and cook over low heat.
Add noodles to sauce, then add cheese.
Mix well.
Serves 8.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in skillet, stir in brown sugar, mustard and salt.
Add cooked carrots, heat, stirring constantly until carrots are glazed, about 5 minutes.

title: apple snack cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar in a large bowl.
Stir well. Combine soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; add pecans, half of morsels and apples.
Spread in a greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining butterscotch morsels on top.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: hot cocoa
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients; simmer 2 minutes.
Add milk; heat.
Before serving, beat until frothy.
If desired, top with marshmallows or whipped cream.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder; set aside. Blend shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture; mix well.
Work in oats, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fannie mae's pickled beets
directions: Mix water, sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add beets; let ingredients come to a good boil.
Place in clean jars and seal.
Let stand for several weeks before serving.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook approximately 4 1/2 hours on high or 8 hours on low.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cut roast in bite-size pieces.
Cut all vegetables into small pieces.
Saute onions.
Put carrots, tomatoes, meat and onions in 1 quart of water and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add mixed vegetables, potatoes, cabbage and green pepper and cook until potatoes are done.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter and sugar and boil 1 minute.
Add milk and powdered sugar.
Mix well until smooth.

title: keith's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large roaster; mix well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Store in a closed plastic or glass container.

title: dough ornaments
directions: Mix flour and salt well, then mix in several drops of food coloring.
Add water slowly until a dough-like consistency is reached.
Mold into holiday shapes or roll the dough to about 1/3 inch thick and cut with cookie cutters.
Make a small hole at the top of each with a straw so the ornament can later be hung by a ribbon once the dough is hard and dry.
Place the ornaments on a cookie sheet and allow a day or two to dry and harden.

title: frozen rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, add sugar; let set until yeast rises.
Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add lard, mix until crumbly.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture; mix well.
Knead 20 or 30 strokes.
Place in greased bowl; let rise 2 hours.
Push down and knead until smooth.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick; cut out biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in freezer bags.
Take out when needed, place in greased pan, put in cold oven.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: cretia's weiners
directions: Mix together.
Put in crock-pot on low.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Add cucumbers and onion.
Add ice cubes and store in refrigerator.
When cucumbers are all gone, you may add more to brine a second or third time.
Great for covered dish or to take to a picnic.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: butterscotch grahams
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with crackers.
Next, combine butter and brown sugar.
Place over heat and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes and stir in nuts.
Quickly spread mixture over crackers with a spoon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan while still warm.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Mix and marinate for about 2 hours.

title: bit-o-chocolate cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add shortening and vanilla; beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Bake at 350°. Makes 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: appleless apple pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cream of tartar together.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Mix butter, cinnamon and crackers into boiled mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Using oblong pan or dish, break cake into chunks and place in pan.
Mix sour cream with pudding by hand; pour over cake.
Spread strawberry and glaze mix over cake.
Place in refrigerator and let cool before eating.
Keep refrigerated all the time.

title: blueberry peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until frothy and well combined.
Add the tapioca and allow to absorb the liquid for 2 minutes.
Beat in brown sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Add peaches and blueberries.

title: blueberry cheese tart
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, butter and nutmeg.
Press into 9-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon peel with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into cookie crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until firm. Cool.
Spread Blueberry Topping over cheesecake.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken souffle(or overnight sandwich)
directions: Place 4 slices of bread in casserole.
Combine next 7 ingredients and spoon onto bread.
Add the other bread slices on top.
Top with milk and eggs.
Cover and keep in refrigerator overnight.
Spoon soup mix over top of sandwiches, then bake 1 hour at 325°.
Add cheese last 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender and drain.
In a saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour to form a paste, then add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add salt and pepper and cover mixture entirely with onion powder.
Stir in cheese until melted. Mix sauce with macaroni and turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole pan. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Combine broth, 1/2 stick melted margarine, soup, salt and pepper to together.
Pour over chicken.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and mash; set aside.
Saute onions in butter until tender. Combine onions, squash, 3/4 cup cracker crumbs, cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin-pecan loaf(with eggnog or hot tea)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° or so for a glass pan).

title: 24 hour party salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook, beating constantly, until thick and smooth.
Remove from stove; add butter and cool.
When cold, fold in whipped cream and drained fruit mixture.
Fruit should be well drained.
Put in refrigerator and let stand (covered with wax paper) for 24 hours.

title: old fashion hot chocolate
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In 2-quart saucepan, add water.
Heat to boil.
Stir.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in milk; heat until hot (do not boil).
Beat until foamy.
Serve immediately.

title: veggie wedgies
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Mix cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley Ranch.
Spread on top of the baked rolls.
Chop vegetables; mix and sprinkle on top, then top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Moisten poultry dressing with chicken stock.
Combine with all but last three ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese, chopped nuts and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: barbecued (baked) ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except the ribs.
Simmer sauce until thick.

title: yummy squares
directions: Mix together cake
mix, butter, pecans and egg.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; spread with fingers.

title: lime cream cooler
directions: In large punch bowl, stir together ice cream, sherbet and milk.
In 1-quart pitcher, stir together lemonade, limeade and water.
Pour over ice cream mixture.
Add ginger ale; stir until slightly mixed.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: eagle brand milk (homemade)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups, same as 1 can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion and water.
Cover; microwave 9 to 10 minutes or until squash is tender.
Mash with potato masher.
Add next 5 ingredients and stir.
Cover and microwave on Medium-high for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cream cheese cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand. Refrigerate overnight. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: egg custard pies
directions: Mix together.
Put into pie shell.
Preheat oven and bake at 350°.
Makes 4 pies.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Form into 40 bite size meatballs, using a full teaspoon for each.
Brown meatballs lightly in oil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain excess fat.

title: corn crackle
directions: Prepare the mix according to package directions.
Spread evenly in well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle with peanuts, cheese and garlic salt; drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes or until crisp and lightly browned.
Immediately cut into squares; cool slightly and remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: special occasion jello
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan to set.

title: chicken bits
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size
pieces.
Dip	in
beaten eggs then in crumbs.	Fry in	hot oil until lightly browned.	Serve hot with dips.
Can be
made
ahead	and
re-heated	in
oven. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: calypso pie
directions: Spread bottom of 9 x 13 pan with Oreo cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup butter. Chill in freezer. Spread softened ice cream over cookie crumbs. Chill in freezer.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt cheese.
Stir in uncooked sausage.
Blend in Bisquick.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 30 minutes.
Very good for a snack.

title: meat dumplings(virtiniai)
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter and add to the ground meat with egg and the spices.

title: lemon cheese tarts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Place pies on cookie sheet and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy white frosting
directions: Beat margarine, shortening and sugar 10 minutes or until sugar is dissolved.
Cook milk and cornstarch together until thickened. Cool to quite warm, then add to sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.

title: five cup salad
directions: Using a cup of each ingredient, combine in a bowl, mixing well. Cover and chill.
Serve topped with maraschino cherry.

title: hot sausage special
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil with salt and pepper.
Add sauce and about 1/2 can of water.
Simmer about 30 minutes on low heat.
Put sausage in a baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into pieces and put into sauce.
Cook on low gas and simmer another 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pie crust(2 crusts)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Mix the last 3 ingredients together, then mix with dry ingredients.

title: spinach salad
directions: Drain and squeeze spinach.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise and onion, then add the soup mix.
Mix all together.
Split bread. Eat with pieces of bread, if desired.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine dates, sugar, salt, butter and water in saucepan. Simmer for 5 minutes; cool.
Add egg.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to date mixture.
Stir to moisten.

title: peanut or pecan fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add cream and mix well.
Add butter and cook over medium heat. Cook to soft ball. Add peanut butter or pecans, marshmallows and vanilla. Beat with electric beater until it begins to turn dull in color.
Dish in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix and store in tight jar.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
May be served hot or cold.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: Shake chicken in bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Save leftover flour.
Fry chicken in butter until brown.
Remove chicken and add onion to the pan; cook until soft.
Stir in reserved flour and cook 1 minute.
Add broth and 2 tablespoons lemon juice and thyme.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring.
Return chicken to pan; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer until chicken is done.
Put chicken on a plate.
Stir remaining 1 tablespoon lemon juice into skillet and pour over chicken.
Serve with lemon wedges as garnish and buttered noodles as a side dish.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Mix and pour into ice cream freezer; finish filling with milk. Strawberries can also be used.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil the eggs.
Cut in half lengthwise; put yellows in bowl. Add heaping tablespoonful of mayonnaise and same amount of sweet pickle relish.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: chocolate mousse delight
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and nuts together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of crust.
Slice peaches in, then add other half of sugar mixture.
Pour cream over all of this.
Bake at 350° until done, 30 or 40 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pare and slice apples; mix with brown sugar in baking pan. Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat egg; mix with flour mixture until crumbly.
Spread over fruit. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: fish packets
directions: Place a 14-inch sheet of heavy-duty foil on the counter for each serving.
Oil or spray the foil.
Place fillet(s) on foil. Add lemon juice and spread over fish.
Cover the fillet(s) with any amount you desire of celery, onion, sliced potatoes, salt and butter.
Add small bits of butter, as desired.
Place on grill over medium-low heat for 35 to 45 minutes.
Open and serve.

title: white chili
directions: Core and coarsely chop tomatoes (makes about 4 cups).
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, heat oil until hot.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in chilies, garlic, cumin, oregano, sugar, cloves, red pepper and the 4 cups tomatoes.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the tomatoes are softened, about 5 minutes. Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, to blend flavors, about 15 minutes.
Add beans and chicken. Cook until hot, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream, shredded Cheddar cheese, diced tomatoes and chopped cilantro, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on pkg. Mix with tuna and soup (may need to thin with a little milk). Drain noodles. Grease casserole dish, layer noodles and tuna mixture ending with tuna mixture. Top with potato chips. Bake at
325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In boiling water, put seasoning (onion, green onions and celery).
Boil 10 minutes.
Put chicken back into boiling water.
Put package of wide noodles in water to boil about 15 minutes.
Drain water from chicken.
Add 1 stick of oleo and 1 can evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Serves 6.

title: christmas snow punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine Hula Punch, Sprite and ice cream.
Stir until well blended.
Chill.
Makes 32 servings.

title: granma vowell's fruit salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to package instructions. Add mayo and cream cheese. Mix well and fold in fruit and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: any flavor cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and egg until smooth.
Add chocolate chips.
Fill cupcake cups with cake mix.
Drop cream cheese filling by heaping teaspoon on cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hurry-up rolls
directions: Whip up all together.
Drop nuts or blueberries in if desired. Spoon in greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cover the beans completely in water and add the grease, salt, sugar and chili powder.
Cook over low heat for 3 or 4 hours.
You may have to add water to keep the beans from burning and sticking. In a separate skillet, brown the hamburger.
Add the hamburger, onion and tomatoes to the beans after they have cooked about 3 hours.
Season to taste with jalapenos.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually, then oil, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple.
Blend dry ingredients into first 6 ingredients. Add nuts.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Nice and moist.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk; bring to a boil, cook for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add oats and peanut butter, mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper, cool.

title: christmas carol cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool 45 minutes and invert on platter.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.

title: thumbprint cookiess
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
With a fork or pastry cutter blend butter into flour, salt, and sugar.
Add almonds and vanilla.

title: tomato-cheese salads
directions: Arrange 3 tomato slices on each of 6 salad plates.
Drizzle with dressing; sprinkle with cheese and onions.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients. Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and then cut into bars.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Brown meat and 1 chopped onion; drain.
Add cans tomatoes and spices.
Bring to boil.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti. Put kidney beans, cheese and onions in separate bowls.
Add chili as a sauce to spaghetti.
Add kidney beans, cheese and onions as a topping.
Very filling.
A different twist on chili with company.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Note:
You will need a very large bowl for final mixture.

title: turtles
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels with milk.
Remove from stove and whip with spoon.
Add pecans until mixed.
Dip out of boiler onto buttered wax paper (about 3 pecans in each).
Let stand while you make chocolate coating.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine 2 cans corn; add milk.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon chicken sauté
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In 10-inch skillet, melt butter until sizzling; add chicken breasts.
Cook over medium heat, turning once until chicken is lightly browned (10 to 14 minutes). In small bowl, combine teriyaki sauce and lemon juice.
Pour around chicken in pan.
Continue cooking, turning once, until chicken is lightly browned (5 to 6 minutes).
Serve over hot cooked rice, if desired.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large skillet cook ground beef and onion till beef is brown, drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning mix and heat through.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs, stir in milk.
Add small amount of tomato sauce mixture to the egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Return all to skillet.
Stir in kidney beans, 1 1/2 cup Monterey Jack and the crushed tacos.
Turn into a 12 by 7 1/2 by 2-inch baking dish.

title: holiday soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a double cooker and simmer 2 hours. (Add wine last.)
Add whipped cream when serving.

title: pizza roll-up
directions: Thaw bread
dough for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Roll out to 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread with tomato paste.
Sprinkle with remaining
ingredients.
Roll
up jelly roll fashion from long side.
Seal.
Place
on
greased baking sheet, seam side down. Brush with warm water.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
Let rise until
almost
double,
about
hour.
Make
shallow slashes across top	at
2-inch
intervals.	Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until done (use cookie sheet).

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Measure 1/2 cup vegetable oil, 2 tablespoons milk together.
Mix dry ingredients with oil mixture until well blended and pat in a 9-inch pie plate.
Poke with fork in bend of plate, at least 6 pricks on bottom and around sides.

title: tarragon-vegetable medley
directions: In microwave dish, combine cauliflower, carrots, onions and water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power, about 5 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender, stirring once.
Add green pepper. Cover and cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes more or until green pepper is tender.
Add olives.
Stir together vinegar, sugar, oil, tarragon and salt.
Stir oil mixture into vegetables.
Cook, covered, on High for 30 seconds more.
Garnish with walnuts.
Serve as a hot vegetable or let the vegetables marinate in the oil and vinegar dressing.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in oil until soft.
Add turkey and cook.
Add a cup of hot water and rice.
Put eggplant in casserole sliced in cubes.
Put mixture over eggplant.
Cover and cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine oil and sugar and mix well. In large bowl, combine all of the dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 of dry ingredients to oil mixture and blend well.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Alternately add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Add carrots and mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13 dish (greased and floured) and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken with lemon-wine sauce
directions: Between waxed paper, pound chicken 1/4 inch thick; season. Coat with flour.
In skillet in 2 teaspoons hot butter or margarine, cook chicken until lightly browned, about 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Remove and keep warm.
Repeat with remaining chicken and butter/margarine as needed.
In cup, stir wine and lemon juice; add to pan drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with parsley. Garnish with capers or lemon slices, if desired.
Serves 4 and only 249 calories per serving.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.

title: funny face desserts
directions: Note:
You will need 4 bowls, a measuring cup and a 1 quart shaker with tight lid.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of oil.
Lay pork chops in bottom of baking dish, then layer potatoes, peas and onion, then add soup over all the dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered with foil.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add oil, eggs and strawberries.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with a mixture of cream cheese and Cool Whip.

title: theresa's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly until eggs are mixed well into mixture.
Heat oven to 350°.
Make mixture into a large round ball and place in pot.
Add a little water to the bottom (less than 1/4 of a cup, just enough to coat bottom of pot). Cover and put in oven.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Take out of oven and serve.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Make a cream sauce of butter, flour, milk, cream and seasonings.
Pour small amount of sauce over egg yolks.
Return to heat and stir until smooth. Add sherry and prepared seafood. Place in buttered scallop shells or shallow casserole. Cover with buttered crumbs and brown in a 350° oven.
May be served with rice or toast points.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Bake at 300° to 325° until brown.

title: beef stew
directions: In large, heavy pan, brown beef in shortening; pour off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients, except onions.
Cover; cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions.
Cook 1 hour more or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate ho ho cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix in jelly roll pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, spread with cream mixture.
Beat mixture for 10 minutes.
Start on low or you will get splattered.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple-cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add sugar and salt; let cool.
Add other ingredients, except whipped cream. Refrigerate until partially set, then fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: graham cracker pecan crisps
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Top with graham crackers.
In boiler, melt margarine.
Add sugar and pecans.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except nuts.
Form into a ball. Roll in crushed nuts.

title: taco cups
directions: Brown hamburg and sausage, drain well. Set aside. Prepare ranch salad dressing. In large bowl mix the hamburg, sausage, chopped vegetables and 1 cup of dressing. Add half of the cheese. Press wonton skins into a cupcake tin and bake at 350° until lightly brown. Just a few min.
Fill cups with meat mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake until cheese melts. Make about 2 dozen.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together with electric mixer at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: peas and peanuts salad
directions: Thaw peas, drain but do not cook.
Mix all ingredients. Marinate overnight.
To vary recipe, add cheese cubes and minced celery.

title: hamburger and bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery. Add other ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
Slice broccoli into bite size pieces. Steam until tender and drain. When the pasta and broccoli have cooled, mix them together with the cheese.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the pasta mixture.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate-coconut slices
directions: Prepare Coconut Filling and chill.
Cream butter and sugar. Blend in egg, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: cheese tuna dip
directions: Combine margarine, flour, salt and dry mustard; stir until blended.
Add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese and tuna.
Mix well.
Add pimiento and parsley; mix lightly.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: low country okra soup with shrimp
directions: Put tomatoes, onion, bell pepper and tomato sauce in saucepan. Simmer, the longer the better (20 to 30 minutes at least).
Cook okra in hot bacon fat in skillet until light brown.
Cook shrimp just until pink.
Add shrimp and okra to sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Can add ham cubes for additional flavor.

title: seafood and vegetables with angel hair pasta
directions: Place seafood and all sliced vegetables in baking dish.
Add salt and pepper, then add Italian dressing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (check vegetables to desired tenderness).
Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions.
Add seafood and vegetables mixture over pasta and add grated Romano cheese.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl and chill until serving time.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Save 1/2 cup asparagus juice and 1/2 cup pea juice.
Combine juices, margarine and flour on top of stove, mixing well until thickened.
Then add cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Layer asparagus, peas and then sauce.
Slice eggs on top; then add cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: white chocolate raspberry swirl cheesecake
directions: In a food processor or in blender at medium speed, blend vanilla wafers and 1/4 cup toasted almonds until fine crumbs form. Mix crumb mixture, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press onto bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
In food processor, blend raspberries until pureed.
Press through fine sieve into 2-quart saucepan to remove seeds.
Stir cornstarch into pureed raspberries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens; boil 1 minute.
Cool.

title: lemon chewies
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and 1 egg; pat in pan. Set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients until creamy. Put on top of first mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pan.
May use any flavor of cake mix.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place deboned chicken in casserole dish.
Top with combined broth, eggs and chicken soup.
Combine all crust ingredients; pour over the chicken mixture.
Pie will make its own crust as it cooks.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: celery and cauliflower
directions: Cut up cauliflower into small pieces and wash very well. Combine all other ingredients together and mix in a very large bowl.
Chill in refrigerator.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: fred's famous deer camp cornbread
directions: Mix meal, milk, eggs, corn, soda, salt and oil.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (or greased iron skillet). Sprinkle with cheese; put meat over cheese and sprinkle onion and peppers.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yummy, yum yum!!!

title: main dish hi fiber casserole
directions: Place all ingredients except cheese in 1 1/2 qt. casserole and mix. Cover casserole and bake 25 minutes in a 350 degree oven. Sprinkle cheese over dish and bake uncovered 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: impossible zucchini-tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch quiche dish.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender).
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 nice servings.

title: pudding crumbs
directions: Mix same as for pie dough.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake lightly (325°).
After it is baked, stir into small pieces like Grape-Nuts.
Use instead of graham crackers for pudding.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples into greased baking dish, 9 x 9-inch.
Crumble flour, sugar, baking powder, egg, salt and cinnamon over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine (more if needed).
Combine other ingredients, add mushrooms and pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: In 2-quart saucepan saute onion in butter.
Add block cheese, soup and cheese sauce.
Melt over low heat, stirring constantly. Add broccoli cuts and garlic powder.
Cook over low heat until broccoli is semi-tender; do not allow to boil.
Serve warm.
Best when served with king size corn chips.

title: peach ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine ingredients; mix well. Freeze to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: baked ham slice
directions: Put ham in shallow baking pan and spread surface with mustard. Drain fruit cocktail and save the syrup.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and spices together.
Stir in fruit syrup and orange juice.
Cook until sauce bubbles and looks transparent. Pour over ham.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Mix well and chill at least 30 minutes.
Make into small balls, flatten and press into small muffin tins as thin as possible.
Fill with fruit mixture.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from broth and debone.
Add 8 ounces of spaghetti to broth.
Cook uncovered until done.
In skillet, saute butter, celery, green pepper and onion.
Set aside. Add all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Drain and mix all vegetables.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and stir until mixture boils.
Take off heat and let cool.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Begin layering crackers and pudding in a deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Begin with crackers on the bottom.)
Pudding should be the last layer. Chill.
Clean and cut strawberries.
Mix with glaze.
Pour over the top.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, cheddar and Roquefort cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce, and seasoned salt. Shape into 2 balls. Roll each ball in pecans and then parsley. Chill.

title: macadamia nut-fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour six (1-cup) fluted tube pans, six 1-cup tube pans or one 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Set pan(s) aside.
In a small saucepan, bring 1/2 cup apricot nectar just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pears and/or apricots and raisins.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: spam melt(delicious)
directions: Halve rolls.
Combine remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of mixture on each half of roll.
Bake in hot oven until rolls are done.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool. Mix dry pudding, powdered sugar and undrained pineapple together. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on cake and refrigerate.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix oil
and
sugar together;
add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients
alternately with zucchini.
Fold in chopped nuts. (Batter will
be
thin.)
Pour
into
x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with rotary beater.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake slowly, about 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: beef, chicken or pork chow mein
directions: In large skillet or wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add sliced meat, cooking until tender.
Season meat with seasoned salt, pepper and garlic powder.
When meat is cooked, remove from pan. Add 1 tablespoon oil to pan and cook vegetables in oil.
Season vegetables with 1/2 teaspoon of soy sauce, oyster sauce and sesame seed oil.
Cook until tender.
Add 2 cups broth and simmer 10 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, cooking 5 minutes more.
Season with salt and pepper.
Return meat to pan, seasoning with oyster sauce and sesame oil.
Thicken with cornstarch, as desired.

title: olive cheese spread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl vigorously stir together cheese, salad dressing and olives.
Turn into one or two jars or crocks; cover tightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Beat well to make smooth batter.
Stir in melted butter.
At the last moment, put in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in hot, well-greased waffle iron.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil and debone chicken breasts.
Reserve chicken broth and use to cook spaghetti.
Drain spaghetti and combine with diced chicken, Ro-Tel and cubed cheeses.
Pour into 1 large Pyrex dish or 2 smaller dishes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until cheese bubbles.
This freezes well.

title: tuna and macaroni salad(weight watchers)
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 1 hour.
Serves 1. This can be doubled or tripled for more people.

title: lil's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand 1 hour, stirring often so juice will form.
Add dry ingredients to apple mixture, then add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Mix by hand, no mixer.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
May be iced, but not necessary.

title: pound cake(low in cholesterol)
directions: Coat bottom of loaf pan with cooking spray and dust with flour. Cream margarine and sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Add egg whites; beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Add vanilla and almond extracts. Beat at low speed until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
With mixer running at low speed, add to creamed mixture, alternating with yogurt, ending with flour.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until done.

title: rise-and-shine refrigerator muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 7 ingredients.
Make a well in the center.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, sugar and oil. Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened (batter should be thick and lumpy).
Fold in raisins or dates and nuts.
Use batter immediately or store in a covered container in refrigerator up to 5 days.

title: lisa's bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except 2 cups of the white flour. Heat milk, syrup and vegetable oil (follow directions on yeast package). Add to flour mixture, then add the egg.
Add the remaining flour until consistency is right.
Let rise until doubled.
Knead and form into loaves.
Let rise again in bread pans, approximately 20 minutes. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Drain asparagus and reserve liquid.
Measure 1 cup liquid, adding water if necessary, and heat.
Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved; refrigerate. When partially set, fold in mayonnaise, whipped cream, salt and lemon juice.
Add asparagus and almonds.
Pour into a 5-cup mold and chill until congealed.
Serve with additional mayonnaise that has been whipped with a little lemon juice.
Serves 12.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a bowl of self-rising flour. Mix to the consistency of biscuits.
Roll out and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: barbecued alaska salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients except salmon.
Generously brush both sides of salmon with mixture.
Place salmon on oiled barbecue, flesh side down.
Baste frequently while cooking.
Barbecue flesh side about 2 minutes.
Turn salmon over carefully.
Baste with sauce.
Make a tent with foil or if using a covered barbecue, cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes, or until salmon flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: whip cream potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes just until done, not too soft.
Chill in the refrigerator.
When thoroughly chilled, grate potatoes in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter.
Cover with whipping cream (unwhipped) and half and half.
Cover with foil.
Allow to refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add flour to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.

title: baked apple wedges
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Sprinkle 1 tablespoon brown sugar over a baking sheet. Combine oats, remaining 2 tablespoons sugar, and spices in the bowl of a food processor and blend until smooth. Add half the almonds and process until finely chopped. Add remaining almonds. Process until coarsely chopped.
Transfer to a shallow bowl.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend softened cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1 large egg until smooth.
Pour mixture into unbaked 10-inch pastry crust. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
In another bowl, blend 3 large eggs, light syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1/2 cup sugar until smooth.
Gently pour mixture over nuts.
Bake on center rack 50 to 60 minutes until center is just set and pastry is golden. Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best brownies
