directions: Stir cocoa and soda together. Blend in 1/3 cup oil. Add water. Stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and rest of oil. Stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla and salt. Blend. Pour into a lightly greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Combine cooked macaroni, tomatoes, broccoli, peas, dressing and basil; toss gently.
Add cheeses; toss lightly and chill.

title: hungarian potatoes and eggs
directions: Mix the bacon fat, sour cream, salt and pepper.
In a greased casserole, layer potatoes, eggs and bacon.
Top each layer with some of the sour cream mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy raspberry cream
directions: In large saucepan, over high heat, heat 3 cups water to boiling point, turn heat to low.
Using large spoon, stir in jello until just dissolved.
Quickly stir in softened vanilla ice cream (cut ice cream in small chunks so it will melt faster).
Mixture should only be lukewarm (very important).
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill overnight.
I use a 2-quart Pyrex oblong dish.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Combine sugar, drink mix and hot water.
Stir well until dissolved.
Cool.
In punch bowl blend sugar syrup, pineapple juice and soda.
Spoon in sherbet.
Makes 22 cups.

title: blueberry special
directions: Mix pudding mix according to directions on package.
In a large
trifle
bowl,
alternate
layers of angel food cake, pudding mix
and
blueberry pie filling until all used up. Top with slices of banana and add whipped cream.

title: ground peanut stew
directions: In a large saucepan brown chicken pieces in hot oil about 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Set aside, reserving drippings.
Add beef, onions and green pepper; cook until beef is brown and onions tender.
Drain and stir in undrained tomatoes, salt and pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add chicken; simmer 20 minutes.
In small saucepan melt peanut butter over low heat.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Return mixture to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes more.
Skim off fat.
Serve with mashed sweet potatoes or hot cooked rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sugar and cocoa powder. Whisk in remaining ingredients except pie crust. Pour chocolate mixture into frozen pie crust. Bake in preheated 350 degrees oven, on preheated baking sheet 30 to 35 minutes until center puffs. Cool completely. Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: fudge
directions: Boil 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter and/or 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Beat very few minutes; pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix
shortening, brown sugar, sugar, oil, egg, milk and vanilla.
Then add flour, soda, cream of tartar, salt, oatmeal and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: honey-oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and honey. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Keep moist in a tightly covered cookie jar or canister. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: ham loaf
directions: Note:
Meat department will mix meats for you.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix noodles with tuna, soup, milk and cheese. Pour into buttered dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake until golden brown.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix as listed above and pour into 2 graham crumb crusts and refrigerate overnight.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Note:
One tablespoon of vinegar added to 1 cup milk, can be used in place of buttermilk.

title: quick potato doughnuts
directions: Prepare potato flakes as package directs for 2 servings; set aside. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, mace, nutmeg and salt.
In large mixer bowl, beat prepared potatoes, eggs, milk, shortening and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half.
On well-floured surface, knead dough to form a smooth ball.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch doughnut cutter; re-roll excess dough.
Fry in hot oil (375°) until golden.
While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Repeat with remaining dough. Makes 3 dozen.

title: lemon grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat whites until stiff.
Cream together the butter, rind and sugar.
Add and mix well the yolks, flour, Grape-Nuts, lemon juice and milk.
Fold in beaten whites.
Pour into a 5-cup souffle dish. Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: macaroni-shrimp salad
directions: * May substitute tiny shrimp, rinsed and drained from can.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Stir all together.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: bugs on a log
directions: Clean celery.
Fill celery with peanut butter.
Put raisins on top.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Mix together and press into pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with semi-sweet morsels, walnuts and flaked coconut.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Makes about 24 bars.

title: crocked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash into quarters and scrape away seeds. Put in crock-pot, skin side down. Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup apple juice or cider over squash. Sprinkle with spice. Cover and cook on low 2 to 4 hours.

title: fried green tomatoes(courtesy of the whistle stop cafe)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix until smooth.
Add additional milk to thin, if needed.
(Batter should be like pancake batter.) Working in batches, dip tomato slices into batter, allowing excess to drip back into bowl.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt until soft ball forms.
Add peanut butter and margarine.
Place pan in cold water.
Beat until it stiffens.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: pasta salad(yields 8 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then pour 1/2
of small bottle of Kraft Italian light dressing (not creamy) over mixture.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Chop celery, onion and green pepper.
Add to drained vegetables.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together water, soup, carrots, onion, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in tortellini and broccoli.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in chicken and heat.
Serve and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Thaw strawberries; drain liquid (SAVE). Mix cake and add strawberries. Bake. Mix frosting according to directions. Substitute liquid from strawberries for water. Frost cake when cool. Decorate with strawberries.

title: cranberries to relish
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large bowl and stir together. Allow to set in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days so the sugar can completely dissolve, stirring once a day.
If you like your cranberries less sweet and more bitter, then reduce the amount of sugar to your liking.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion and beef slightly.
Add chili powder, tomato soup and kidney beans.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: oyster cracker mix
directions: Pour oil into large cooking (baking) pan.
Pour in crackers and coat real good with oil.
In bowl, mix well other ingredients and add to crackers.
Mix well.
Put in oven for 15 minutes at 225°.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Cool, store and eat!!

title: veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Keep refrigerated until serving. Serve with carrot sticks, celery sticks, cherry tomatoes, radishes, zucchini, cucumber sticks, green peppers and cauliflowerets.

title: salami triangles
directions: Blend cheese, horseradish and Tabasco.
Spread 12 slices salami with cheese mixture.
Top with another slice of salami; more cheese and a third slice of salami.
You can chill them at this time to aid in slicing.
Cut each circle into quarters. Makes 48 triangles.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook
chicken
until
real tender.
Remove all skin and bone. Cut chicken fine with scissors.
Mix 1 cup celery and 1 cup pickles
to every 2 cups of chicken.
Add sugar and mayonnaise; mix well.
This should be nice and firm.

title: barbecue beans with beef
directions: Brown ground beef or chuck, onion and bell pepper in skillet and drain grease.
Add pork and beans, mustard, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Mix all ingredients and place in Pyrex dish. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter in large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, stir until well mixed.
Butter bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan and press mixture into pan with a buttered spatula. After cools, cut into squares.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, butter and nuts together until crumbly. Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions according to directions.
Add chopped peppers, cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 of the grated cheese. Season to taste.
Put in a baking pan and top with crushed potato chips and remainder of the cheese.
Bake until well blended and crust is browned at approximately 350°.

title: cabbage salad(3 week cole slaw)
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, green pepper and carrot.
In saucepan, mix sugar, vinegar, oil and celery seed, bringing to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Pour into airtight container.
This will keep about 1 month refrigerated.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix all together. Sprinkle over 5 medium potatoes and 2 or 3 tablespoons grated onion in a 2-quart baking dish. Do this in alternate layers. Then add 1 1/2 cups hot water and 3 tablespoons butter. Make sure mixture is dissolved. If you need to, you can add a
little more hot water. Bake at 350° until tender (approximately 1 hour).

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese together.
Add salt to flour.
Add to the cheese mixture.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: retha's christmas hard candy
directions: Add drops of food coloring while cooking.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Cut up vegetables into medium pieces.
Cover with water in a large pot.
Bring to boil; add soup mix and tomatoes.
Reduce heat and cook until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Wesson oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to mixture and stir in apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This can be baked in a Pyrex dish.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Beat eggs slightly; gradually add sugar, oil, water and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, spices, raisins and nuts (if you are using them).
Grease 1 1/2 dozen muffin cups and fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pot of gold biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients and cut in oil. Stir in sweet potatoes.
Add juice and honey and stir to a smooth dough.
When firm enough to handle, knead briefly (about 30 seconds).
Pat to a 1/2-inch thickness and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Bake on an oiled baking sheet or pan for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
12 biscuits.

title: chicken with spinach noodles
directions: Cook vegetables in some of the chicken broth until tender. Cook noodles in rest of broth.
Noodles should absorb most of the liquid.
Add soup and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms with juice, water chestnuts, vegetables and cut up chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Put into 3 well buttered casserole dishes. Bake at 350° until hot.
This is better made the day before and freezes well.
Serves 20.

title: butterscotch chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in butterscotch chips and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Combine juices; add sugar, milk and salt and freeze.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with raw celery, carrots, cauliflower and broccoli.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
In the bottom of a pie plate, shred lettuce, chop tomatoes and slice the jar of jumbo olives.
Grate Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Pour remaining mixture on top.

title: mints
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, flavoring and syrup.
Divide and add colors.
Work in very good.
Can be put in molds or make your own design.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased and corn meal sprinkled pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: Run cold water over dried beef and divide into 6 clumps. Place on bottom of baking dish.
Put chicken breasts on top. Place 2 slices of bacon on each breast.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Mix mushroom soup and sour cream and pour over the chicken.
Bake an additional 25 minutes.

title: bran refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour hot water over margarine, bran flakes, sugar and salt. Allow to cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast dissolved in lukewarm water.
Add flour; beat thoroughly and knead.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Can be left overnight.
Remove and make into rolls.
Let rise again about 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: arlene's burritos
directions: Place hamburger meat in a large skillet.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, chili powder and onion; brown together.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chiles; stir well.
Lower fire, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir once.
Add sour cream and simmer 5 minutes.
Place desired amount on tortillas.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, olives and picante sauce to taste.
Fold and enjoy.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix until all is moist.
Put in loaf pans greased with vegetable oil.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: pineapple sweet n' sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add bouillon; simmer 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and pineapple chunks. Blend together next 5 ingredients and add to mixture.
Cook, stirring frequently, for about 10 minutes or until thickened. Serve over rice.

title: gram's dropped sand tart cookies
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in vanilla.
Stir baking powder and flour together and beat into creamed mixture.

title: shrimp gruyere
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter with olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, green onions, parsley and chervil and saute until mushrooms are tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute until just pink, about 3 minutes.
Add wine; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Remove shrimp and mushrooms using slotted spoon and keep warm.
Stir in cream and remaining 1 tablespoon of butter.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens.
Return shrimp and mushrooms to skillet.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: pocket pizza
directions: Roll out 1
loaf
bread
dough	and
fit in 9 x 13-inch greased cake
pan.	Fry
onions and peppers and drain.
Spread all ingredients
on
dough,
covering
them
with the cheeses. Roll out second	loaf
of bread and cover.
Brush with oil and top with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini loaf
directions: Beat eggs well, then beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 3 smaller ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour plus.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: 72 market street meat loaf(from 72 market street in venice)
directions: Saute shallots in 1 tablespoon butter with thyme, bay leaf and black pepper.
Add white wine and simmer over high heat until reduced to glaze.
Add beef stock or veal stock and simmer over high heat until reduced by 1/3 or 1/2.
Stir in remaining 1 tablespoon butter and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir until butter melts and sauce blends in.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve with meat loaf.
Makes 1 cup.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together soup mix and stuffing.
Add to spinach.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with additional cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender. Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Beat cottage cheese and 2 tablespoons oil with a rotary beater until fluffy. Mix in chopped onion. Mix flour and seasonings. Place a layer of sliced potatoes in casserole. Cover with a layer of cottage cheese. Sprinkle with seasoned flour. Repeat layers, ending with a layer of potatoes. Pour milk over potato-cheese layers. Mix breadcrumbs with Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle over potatoes. Dot with margarine. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon-raisin scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pam spray 12 medium muffin cups.

title: pumpkin jumbos
directions: Combine raisins and water in saucepan.
Bring to boiling and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid; cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla 3 minutes at high speed of mixer.
Alternately add dry ingredients in fourths with the raisin liquid.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased sheet, about 2 inches apart.

title: crunchy apple cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix; sprinkle nuts over butter.
Bake at 375 degrees F for 45 minutes or until top is brown and filling bubbles.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 10 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pepperidge chicken pie
directions: Mix stuffing mix with 1 stick melted margarine and chopped onion.
Layer the following:
1/2 stuffing mix, 2 cups chicken, soup, and remaining stuffing mix.
Pour broth on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place pastry in pan.
Make some little holes with a fork in bottom of pastry.
Cover with slices of smoked bacon and add slices of Gruyere.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt, mustard, onion and the 2 tablespoons vinegar in a blender or food processor.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly.
Add 3 tablespoons vinegar and celery seed.
Continue beating until thick.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: carolyn's easy peach pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Combine ingredients.
Top with a little extra Cheddar cheese and bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: freezer sweet corn
directions: Combine ingredients; cook for 10 minutes (do not boil).
Let cool.
Put in freezer bags and freeze.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, garlic and oregano together. Cook jumbo pasta shells for stuffing as directed on box.
Stuff the cooked shells with the cheese mixture, place in casserole dish and cover with prepared spaghetti sauce.
Cover with foil.

title: fern's gazpacho
directions: In a blender, puree tomatoes, onion, green pepper and cucumber.
Add tomato juice, cumin, garlic, salt and pepper.
Put in a bowl; cover and chill.
Before serving, add oil and vinegar. Serve accompanied by side dishes of chopped vegetables.
Garnish with croutons.

title: quick soup
directions: Bring water, juice and bouillon cubes to boil, then add macaroni slowly.
Stir occasionally.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: italian goulash
directions: Cook hamburger until done and drain.
Cook rotini until tender, then drain.
Put in 3-quart pan and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Beat all ingredients until fluffy.

title: honey-dipped chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg wash and bread in Italian bread crumbs. (For best results, bread twice.)
Fry in cast-iron skillet to light brown.
Be careful not to break the coating.
Place on baking sheet.
Squeeze honey over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven 10 minutes.

title: grandma's sour cream meatballs
directions: Using medium saucepan, fill halfway with water.
Bring to just below boil.
Mix ground meat, onions, peppercorns, salt, pepper, bread and eggs.
Roll into meatballs.
Place in hot water with onion powder for about 1/2 hour.
Make sure water just covers meatballs.
Add sour cream and potatoes; simmer another 3 hours. Refrigerate in pot overnight.
Reheat and serve with green or orange vegetable and applesauce.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until light brown.
Drain fat.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Make a well in the dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and spices.
Stir just to mix.
Cover and store.
Will keep as long as 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add chopped dates and cook 3 minutes (mash dates).
Add remaining ingredients.
Let cool and roll in coconut.

title: honey graham crackers
directions: Blend all ingredients together (3 minutes).
Divide in half; place half on ungreased baking sheet (17 x 14-inch); flatten out and roll out, flouring glass so as not to stick to rolling pin or glass.
Score into 2-inch squares.
(Leave in place.)
Prick all over with fork.
Bake in middle of preheated oven at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until browned.
Remove and cut along scored lines while hot.
Let cool on baking sheet.
They crisp while they cool. Watch carefully when baking.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in pan and sprinkle salt over; mix.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out water.
Boil rest of ingredients: green pepper, carrots, sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed, then cool and cover the cabbage.
Freeze the combination.
It can be refrozen for another time if not all used.

title: best ever blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together eggs, milk and margarine.
Stir in sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Do not overmix.
Fill greased muffin tin, each 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: spanish rice
directions: Add ground beef and Rice-A-Roni and mix.
Add seasonings; simmer on low heat until all liquid is absorbed.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and half of shredded cheeses on top of mixture.
Alternate with mixture and cheeses again.
Bake at 350°.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water; drain off most of water when potatoes are tender.
Mash potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed with mixer until creamy and smooth.
Stir in chives, then spoon into a lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 30 minutes.

title: beef stew with vegetables
directions: Cut beef in 1-inch cubes; dredge in 1/4 cup of flour.
Turn temperature control to 375° and preheat skillet.
Add fat, then brown meat well on all sides.
Add next 5 ingredients and stir to mix well.
Turn temperature control to 175° and cook, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Add carrots and onions. Cover and cook 30 minutes longer, until meat and vegetables are tender.
Add oregano and peas and heat to boiling.
Blend remaining 1/4 cup flour and cold water.
Add to stew; cook and stir until thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cool lime cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons Equal spoonful in bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan or 8-inch round cake pan; pat evenly on bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of pan. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 8 minutes.

title: mexican burrito dinner
directions: Use box of burrito dinner.
Use deer meat, ground turkey or Maverick lite beef.
After browning, drain off all fat.
Follow rest of directions.
Serve with fat-free sour cream, picante sauce, fat-free shredded cheese and diced tomatoes and onions.
Serve with Guiltless Gourmet nacho chips and yellow Mexican rice.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a glass mixing bowl. Cook 7 to 9 minutes on High; mixture should be bubbling and peanuts browned.
Quickly stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir quickly, just until mixture is foamy.
Pour immediately onto greased cookie sheet. Let cool 30 minutes.
Break up peanut brittle and store in an airtight container.

title: prime brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator. Bake brisket in marinade liquid at 275° for 1 hour per pound. This tastes like prime rib.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat vigorously with spoon until mixed.
Stir in bananas and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all except nuts.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Shape into ball. Roll in nuts and chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, spinach and soup mix together until well combined.
Hollow out loaf of bread; cut into cubes the bread removed from center.
Clean and cut up any vegetables of your choice.
Fill hollow bread with dip mixture just before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all and chill.
Use any type of crackers.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo or butter in deep baking dish; set aside.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Add prepared fruit (if canned, drain) on top of batter mix.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in large pan.
Over top spread dressing of mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese, mixed.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: four bean salad
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and oil for 5 minutes.
Cool well. Thoroughly rinse all beans and drain.
Mix with celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix all in a ceramic or glass container (not metal).
Pour cold dressing over all and refrigerate overnight. Will keep 1 month in refrigerator.

title: wacky cupcakes
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 42 cupcakes.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Layer the pork chops in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then layer potatoes on top of pork chops and onions on top of potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour water over the ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for about 1 hour.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Thaw spinach.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Spread thin layer on a tortilla and roll it up.
Wrap plastic wrap around it and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Remove from refrigerator, slice in 1-inch slices.
Place on cut sides on serving tray.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake in a 250° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add onions.
Cook until transparent.
Add garlic, basil, oregano, salt, tomatoes and paste.
Cook few minutes, stirring.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat cream of chicken soup, milk, Velveeta and green chilies in top of double boiler.
Brown the ground beef and onion well; add salt and pepper.
Warm tortillas in grease.
Grate Longhorn cheese.
Fill with meat mixture and grated cheese.
Roll up; cover with cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Marinate meat for 48 hours.
Punch holes in meat with fork on both sides.
Cook on high or medium high (grill closed) for 6 to 8 minutes on each side.
May freeze and reuse marinade up to 3 times.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a saucepan. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together cake mix, butter, nuts and remaining milk.
Press half of the dough in pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust and cover chips with caramel mixture.
Crumble remaining dough on top.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes in 350°.
Refrigerate 30 minutes to set caramel layer.

title: cheese twist sticks
directions: Sift all dry ingredients and cut in cheese and butter.
Add ice water and roll to a thickness of 1/8-inch.
Cut in strips and twist.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Cut breasts in 2 x 1-inch chunks.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken, bake another 10 minutes.
Broil for 10 minutes until brown.
Serve with rice or linguini.

title: flash boy-ar-dee gumbo
directions: Combine salsa, beans, chili seasoning and water in crock-pot. Cook, covered, on high for 1 hour.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook additional 30 minutes, then add okra.
Cook additional 15 minutes and add corn.
Cook additional 15 minutes and add rice.
Stir thoroughly; turn off crock-pot.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Keep lid on crock-pot throughout cooking and after the rice is added.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugars:
add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and chopped nuts.
Divide dough into equal parts - shape into long rolls.
Wrap and put into refrigerator over night.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake on ungreased cookie sheet 5-7 minutes at 425°.

title: fruit punch for 50
directions: Combine the frozen fruit concentrates in a large container. Stir to mix.
Add water.
Best to make ahead and freeze.
Then take out of freezer and partially unthaw before using.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together and let set.
Mix the remaining ingredients; fold in milk mixture.
This makes two 9-inch pies.
Good with graham cracker crusts.
May be frozen.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Mix syrup and sugar in large saucepan. Cook, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil. Stir in peanut butter; mix well. Add Rice Krispies and press mixture into jelly roll.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cut turkey breast into bite sizes.
Add remaining ingredients and just enough Hellmann's to make mixture stay together.

title: diabetic easter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Add milk.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, then add vanilla and sweetener.
Spread on foil.
Chill. Cut in pieces or form in egg-shaped balls.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add picante and soup.
Heat thoroughly; serve with chips.

title: red potato salad
directions: Wash and dice potatoes.
Do not peel.
Cook, drain and cool. Hard boil the eggs and mash (very fine).
Chop the onions.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, onion, chilies, milk, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add Doritos; top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: have another helping squash
directions: Fry bacon until crisp (drain, then crumble).
Saute squash and onions in bacon drippings (8 to 10 minutes).
Combine egg and sour cream, add to squash mixture, stir in bacon and cheese. Pour into shallow 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
You may garnish with shredded cheese or a sprinkling of paprika.

title: dried beef-broccoli casserole
directions: Blend flour into 2 tablespoons butter in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add remaining ingredients except remaining butter and bread crumbs, stirring well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar;
add egg and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Drop in teaspoon size balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Squeeze margarine in the bottom of a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Put
a layer of bread, with crusts removed, in bottom of pan.
Squeeze margarine on top of bread.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture on top also.
Layer more bread and repeat.

title: majestic pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients thoroughly.
Add lemon juice last. Pour in cooled shells.
Chill and serve.

title: black bottom
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, milk, salt and egg yolks in double boiler until thick.
Remove from fire; add gelatin which has been soaked in water.
Divide mixture and grated chocolate to one half.
Cool other half before adding beaten egg whites.
Let mixtures set in separate bowls in refrigerator until they begin to thicken.
Beat each mixture until smooth.
Pour chocolate mixture into baked graham cracker shell.
Carefully pour white mixture on top.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours.
Serve with whipped cream and grated chocolate.

title: hot fudge
directions: Melt chips first, then add remaining ingredients.
It's great!

title: whipped syllabub(serving size: 6)
directions: Measure the whipping cream into the large mixing bowl and beat it with a wire whisk or eggbeater until it is thick.
Set the bowl aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans or 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch) pans.
Bake for 70 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: raspberry meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add raspberry gelatin and sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved.
Mix in vinegar; fold in chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto brown paper on cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave cookies in oven 20 minutes longer.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Season to taste (salt and pepper, etc.).
Dip tortillas in hot oil for 5 seconds to soften.
Roll hamburger, shredded Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese in tortilla (about 1 tablespoon of meat).
Line casserole dish with enchiladas.
Pour sauce over, making sure it goes between enchiladas.

title: party pizza appetizers
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Separate each biscuit into 3 pizza rounds. Spread with mixture. Put pizzas on cookie sheet and freeze. Remove from cookie sheet and store in
plastic bags. Bake frozen pizzas at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: pasta primavera salad
directions: Mix pasta and vegetables in large bowl.
Add nonfat dressing; mix lightly.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients together until desired thickness.

title: pot roast
directions: Season flour with basil, oregano and Nature's seasonings to taste.
Coat the roast on both sides.
Melt the butter, or put the oil in a Dutch oven on top of the stove.
Sear the roast well on both sides.
When the roast is brown, cover it with water.
Add beef bouillon, tomato sauce and onion.
Cook on medium, uncovered, for about 2 hours, adding water as needed.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook until meat falls apart and vegetables are done.

title: german chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until all dry ingredients are moistened.	Press in bottom of greased 9x13x2 pan.	Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add eggs and mashed bananas.
Batter should appear lumpy.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake(vera routon)
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; cream well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating slightly after each one.
Dissolve soda in the teaspoon of hot water.
Add to buttermilk.
Add milk and flour, alternately to butter mixture.
Beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, vanilla and coconut.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Decrease heat to 325° and bake 1 hour.
Let cake rest in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out and cover with cloth until cool.

title: instant dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns or bread.

title: florida spinach salad
directions: Just before serving, combine spinach, orange sections and cashews with Florida Blue dressing.
Serves 6 to 8 (dressing).
In electric blender, combine Blue cheese, salad oil, grapefruit juice and seasoned salt; cover.
Blend until smooth or use a small bowl and an electric mixer.
Stir in sour cream.
Cover.
Chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cream cheese pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add 1 egg to mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix well in large bowl the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift in flour and baking powder.
Mix again. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken(microwave)
directions: Place chicken in microwave dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and ginger.
Top with celery. Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 16 minutes, turning dish once.
Mix pineapple juice with brown sugar, water, soy sauce, vinegar and cornstarch in microwave measuring cup. Microwave on High for 3 minutes, until mixture thickens, stirring once.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Add the pineapple chunks and red pepper.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for another 6 to 8 minutes, until chicken is tender and juices run clear when chicken is pierced with fork.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and salsa together. Chill and add cheese. Sprinkle on top.
Dip with chips and enjoy.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: muffins
directions: Melt margarine.
Blend all together and put in muffin pan. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, margarine, vegetable oil, sour milk and vanilla. Add zucchini, flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Chocolate chips are optional. They make the cake very rich. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13 dish.

title: easy graham bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread mixture into a well-greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake pulls from sides of pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine cooked rice, milk, pudding mix and egg in saucepan. Stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Cool 5 minutes stirring twice.
Pour into bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in all ingredients together.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Dip chicken in slightly beaten egg and breadcrumbs.
Place in frying pan in margarine.
Brown and place in buttered casserole. Drain mushrooms and reserve juice.
After frying chicken, add mushroom juice and equal amount of water.
Saute in frying pan. Place a layer of chicken, top with 1/2 mushrooms and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Pour mushroom juice over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Preheat oven roaster to 500°. Brown beef in shortening in an enamel pan or the roaster.
Add remaining ingredients except celery.
Stir well and cover.
Set temperature to 400° and cook until all vegetables and rice are tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add celery the last 20 minutes of cooking time.
Keep hot. Yields 50 people, 3/4 cup serving.

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes; cook until almost done.
Put in a baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and heat until you can stir together.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jimmy carter fish
directions: Cut catfish or bass into French fry strips.
Marinate overnight in Heinz 57 or A.1.
Coat with Bisquick or pancake mix in paper bag (shaken).
Fry in hot oil.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring corn syrup, sugar and salt to a boil over medium heat. Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Gradually pour over popped corn.
Toss until coated and shaped into balls or press in a mold.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Chop vegetables. Combine with onion soup mix and water in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, cover, lower heat and simmer until vegetables are done.
Add can of vegetables and V-8 juice.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic and bouillon.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix crumbs with margarine and spread 1/2 over bottom of dish. Mix cabbage and onion; spread over crumbs.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, salt, pepper and milk; pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Best if cheese does not get crusty on top.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare muffin mix according to package directions.
Add cheese and set aside.

title: mini cream cheese cupcakes
directions: You will also need foil-lined cupcake holders.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil cloves and cinnamon in water for 5 minutes.
Add tea, sugar and juices from the lemons and oranges.
Drink warm or cold.

title: pineapple-cheese delight
directions: Heat juice from cans of pineapple.
Mix 4 teaspoons sugar, salt and flour and beat into heated juice.
Remove from heat.
Add beaten eggs and beat entire mixture.
If eggs are small, use a little more flour.
Chill.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces; saute in large pot; add celery and onions.
Saute until tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and tomatoes. Drain clams.
Add enough water to broth to make 4 cups liquid. Add this to vegetables with salt, pepper and thyme.
Simmer covered 35 minutes.
Add clams and simmer another 30 minutes.

title: heavenly pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the 1 cup of boiling water.
Add the pineapple and lemon juices.
Chill until thickened.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir well; cool before putting in pie shell.

title: zeese challah *
directions: Measure yeast, salt, honey and hot water into large bowl and stir.
Mix in 2 cups flour, oil and eggs.
Add 4 more cups flour, 1 cup at a time; beat each cup in well with wooden spoon. Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour onto clean hard surface.
Knead in enough remaining flour to make dough silky and resilient, but still soft, 8 to 10 minutes.
Additional kneading after silky state.
Place dough into bowl with 1 tablespoon oil; turn to oil all sides.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400. Place muffins on baking dish. Spread two Tbsp of pizza sauce in the center of English muffin halves. Arrange veggies over sauce. Combine mozzarella, parmesan and herbs. Sprinkle over veggies. Bake 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: kathy's no-fail bread
directions: Put milk and butter
in saucepan and swirl until butter is melted.
Beat eggs well with
mixer
and
stir in sugar and egg mixture.
Add milk and
butter mixture; place all in large Tupperware bowl.
Add flour, a
little
at a time, until dough is soft, smooth and elastic.
You may do this with large spoon at first
and then by hand
in
bowl.	Rub
small
amount
of vegetable oil thoroughly around
the
inside
of
a metal bowl (not aluminum).

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend.
Mold into a ball or logs.
Decorate with sliced olives and parsley sprigs.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Add cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add 2 beaten eggs, buttermilk, soda, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour in a greased sheet cake pan, 16 x 11-inch.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 24 servings.
Have icing ready.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll cookie dough to fit pizza pan. Bake until done (5 to 8 minutes).
Mix xxx sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Spread on cooled cookie crust.
Mix fresh strawberries with glaze and spread over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, blend until creamy.
Chill.

title: ritz cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Make about 65 crackers. Melt white chocolate and shortening in top of double boiler.
Carefully dip peanut butter crackers into chocolate, covering them completely. Put on wax paper to cool.

title: false mince pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt
butter.
Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar, cooking oil, eggs and vanilla. Thoroughly mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until light tan.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.
Good.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix until smooth. Pour into 3 or 4 loaf pans. Fill pans about half full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: surprise salad
directions: Add sugar to pineapple and bring to boil.
Pour all ingredients except whipping cream into Jell-O mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Mix cream with jellied mixture; let set again for a short time.
Stir before serving.

title: pina colada frosting
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add sugar gradually.
Mix until creamy.
Add Cool Whip; fold in pineapple and pecans.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix ingredients and place in a gallon jug.
Finish filling jug with water.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer for 6 to 8 hours before use.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: You will need nonstick spray.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar, pineapple and flour.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Let cool.
Whip the cream and add to the mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: herbed rib roast
directions: Cut 15 slits in the roast; insert garlic.
Combine salt, pepper, basil, parsley and marjoram; rub over roast.
Place fat side up on a rack in a roaster.
Bake, uncovered at 325° for 2 to 2
1/2 hours or until meat reaches the desired doneness.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler. Add a little milk and blend until smooth.
Add rest of milk and cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Then place over boiling water; cover and cook 15 minutes with occasional stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve warm or cold as pudding sauce.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
(I use over yellow cake.)

title: shortcut chili sauce
directions: Pour salt over all ingredients and let stand overnight. Drain.
Place in large kettle and add 2 cups sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons pepper, 1 1/2 teaspoons pickling spice (tied in cheesecloth) and 1 cup white vinegar.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Ladle into jars, seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Using shallow platter (round, about 12-inches), layer ingredients in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: meat pie
directions: Mix all purpose and self-rising flour with warm water and roll out on a floured surface.
Cut in squares.
Cook meat.
Season with a lot of pepper.
Put meat in center of square.
Roll up until it laps over.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put in pan on stove the sugar, Karo and milk.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Put in dish and let get cool.

title: french toast
directions: Beat
eggs well; add milk, vanilla, cinnamon and sugar. Melt butter
in	medium	heat
skillet.	Place
bread
in egg mixture; turn
so
that
both sides are covered with mixture. Place	bread in	skillet.
When edges turn golden brown, turn bread.
If skillet becomes dry while cooking, add more butter. Serve with maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: dump cake
directions: In a baking dish, layer the cherries, pineapple and cake mix; melt butter and pour over mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chinese barbecue
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and marinate for at least 5 hours or overnight in the refrigerator. You can either fry the meat or grill it.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Wrap each piece of chicken with slice of beef and 1/2 strip of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place in baking dish.

title: cheese and rice casserole
directions: Mix 1 cup grated cheese with 2 cups cooked rice, sour cream and green chilies.
Sprinkle with other cup of grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: quick raisin bread(a very old family recipe)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add milk to eggs.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients and mix just until smooth.
Stir in melted fat and raisins (and nuts if desired).
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken broth, chicken, vegetables and soup; pour into a casserole dish.
Mix flour, milk and margarine (can use wire whisk; this works well).
Pour over chicken mixture, but don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hassel back potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes or leave skins on and scrub with brush.
With sharp knife, slice each potato crosswise every 1/4 to 1/2-inch, but not quite all the way through.
Place potatoes in a buttered pie plate.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons of melted butter and sprinkle with salt.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over potatoes and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Baste with butter from pie plate. Bake 20 minutes or until tender.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix pudding and pie filling and jello.
Add water and boil for 5 minutes; cool (this will not be thick).
Add sliced berries, chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: mexico chiquito's cheese dip
directions: Melt margarine over low heat; add all spices and simmer 5 minutes.
Add flour and stir well, until a paste is formed.
Add Ro-Tel and raise heat to medium.
Add 1/2 of milk and stir until hot.
Add chopped cheese and cook until melted (stirring frequently).
May need to use a mixer to make smooth.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: banbury tarts
directions: Mix well and put in unbaked pastry tart shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden.

title: italian ragout
directions: Saute sausage (without casing) in olive oil.
Add peppers, onion and mushrooms.
Saute until onion is translucent and other vegetables are tender.
Pour sauteed mixture into large saucepan. Add stewed tomatoes and squash.
Simmer until squash is tender. Serve over rice or pasta or with Italian bread.

title: party pickles
directions: Dry pickles.
Cover with cream cheese.
Wrap with ham. Refrigerate and slice before serving.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, 1 gallon water and lime.
Let set overnight; drain.
Add the salt.
Let set 4 hours; drain.
Cover with water; let set 2 hours, drain.
Add 1 gallon water and the alum.
Boil and set 20 minutes; drain.
Put the vinegar in kettle with the pickling spices and sugar.
Simmer 15 or 20 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: banana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set until thick.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Mix everything together until well blended.
Shape dough about 2 inches long and about 1/2-inch wide.
Dip cookie in milk, then sesame seed.
Place in ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tom's pickles
directions: Remove all the pickles from the jar and pour off the liquid. Slice the pickles and return to jar.
When the jar is half full, cover with 1 cup of the sugar, then place the rest of the pickles in the jar and cover with the other cup of sugar.
Add 2 tablespoons of vinegar, then recap the jar.
Invert the jar and leave for a day.
Turn it over for a day and then back again. Keep repeating for 4 or 5 days, then enjoy them.

title: gussie's bread pudding
directions: Break eggs in pan; beat them, then put sugar in.
Put milk and water in.
Add vanilla, pineapple with juice and French bread. (Soak bread pieces and put in before pineapple.)
Cut oleo on top. When butter melts; stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until well done.
Chop tomatoes, onions, green peppers and cucumbers.
Cut cheese in square blocks, using the amount you desire.
Use mayonnaise as you desire.
Make and let stand in a covered dish (all except mayonnaise).
Put mayonnaise in when ready to eat.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Combine sauerkraut, onion and brown sugar.
Toss lightly with fork.
Use 9 x 13 baking dish.
Put kraut on bottom, then pork chops and top with soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: joanne's quick chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chili mix and water.
Cook down.

title: salmon imperial
directions: Spread shallots on fillets.
Drizzle oil on fillets.
Put 3 slices tomato on each and 3 slices lemon on each fillet.
Place wine over fillets and sprinkle with parsley.
Heat oven to 475°. In greased pan, cook fillets uncovered for 6 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and salt; set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O and boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice and rind, cinnamon and cloves.
Chill until thick.
Fold in cranberries, oranges and nuts.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Place oil, banana and eggs into another bowl.
Beat until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Then fold liquid ingredients into the dry very gently.
Thump pan to allow air bubbles to escape.
Grease and flour pans (loaf).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: georgia cracker chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken; place in baking dish.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Sprinkle finely crumbled crackers over chicken.
Melt butter and pour over crackers and chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 375° oven.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Fry bacon.
Pour most of the grease off, but leave some in pan.
Set bacon aside to cool.
In same pan, add potatoes and onions.
Cook until brown.
Pour beaten eggs over mixture, then cook until almost set.
Add crumbled bacon.
Listed are some other ingredients you can use.
We always use cheese.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine cheese and croutons in dish.
Mix six other ingredients and pour in pan.
Crumble bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add eggs and flour.
Mix extracts and blend well.
Spread batter in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Cut surface of batter to make 28 squares.
Spoon pie filling in center of each square. During baking, batter puffs up around pie filling.
Bake at 350° or 40 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cut in squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: carciofi imbottiti con granchio(artichokes stuffed with crab)
directions: Boil or steam artichokes.
Cook until hearts are easily pierced; rinse under cold water.
Invert and drain.

title: beefy mexican corn bread
directions: Combine 1 cup cornmeal, salt and soda in large bowl; mix well. Add eggs, milk, corn and bacon drippings until mixed smooth; set aside.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of cornmeal into skillet (10-inch oiled).
Pour half of batter into skillet; sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Top with leaf onion; sprinkle pepper on top.
Pour remaining batter over peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add cream and mix well. Beat eggs one at a time and combine singularly with the cream mixture.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until firm.

title: pinwheel appetizers
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, onion, peppers and celery with Valley Ranch powder.
Spread mixture on tortillas and roll up jelly roll fashion tightly.
Chill in refrigerator for a few hours.
Cut off ends of each roll and discard.
Slice tortillas into desired size slices and place on serving tray.
Sprinkle with paprika to make pretty.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cook slowly the margarine, dates, egg and sugar. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix well. Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: 8-minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into pie crusts.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.

title: cabbage and tomatoes
directions: Cook cut up cabbage in a 10-inch stainless steel skillet (put about 1 inch of water in skillet).
Cover skillet; let cabbage get tender.
Add fresh sliced tomato wedges.
Cook bacon strips until crisp in microwave; crumble bacon into cabbage-tomato mixture. Cover skillet; cook on medium or low heat until tomatoes are soft. (Total cooking time is about 35 minutes.)

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Cut in butter with knife.
Make a well in the center and gradually mix in just enough buttermilk to make a soft but firm dough.
Add raisins.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco, add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour and soda, add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut and nuts, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, to which you have added 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peppered pork chops
directions: Coat chops with pepper and thyme.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chops; cook to brown one side (2 to 3 minutes).
Turn to brown other side.
Remove chops from pan; keep warm.
Deglaze skillet by adding Worcestershire sauce to hot pan; stir constantly to remove any pan juices cooked to bottom.
Pour accumulated juices over chops; serve immediately.

title: pot roast
directions: Note:
If using crock-pot (slow cooker), also add sliced carrots and sliced potatoes.

title: crispy taco turnovers
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion and garlic in heavy frying pan.
Add salt and chili powder.
Blend well.
Place 1/2 cup of the beef filling, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup tomatoes onto one-half of each tortilla.
Fold other half over filling, pressing it down to remove any air pockets. Pour oil into large skillet to 1/4-inch depth.
When oil is hot, place filled tortillas into pan a few at a time.
Saute over medium to high heat until golden on each side, about 45 seconds per side.
Remove from pan onto paper towel.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: joe theismann's super bowl slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mince green onion wedges and put them along with all other ingredients into blender or food processor. Blend all ingredients until smooth. Toss dressing onto cabbage and green peppers.

title: stamberg family's cranberry relish
directions: Grind berries and onion together in meat grinder.
Stir in sour cream, sugar and horseradish.
Freeze.
Thaw and remix before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: In covered blender container blend all ingredients at high speed just until finely minced.
Remove to bowl.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.
Can be made a day or two before using.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute steak until done, but not brown; set aside.
Add the Puritan oil to a separate skillet.
Saute onion and peppers in oil for about 4 minutes.
Mix the cornstarch, water, bouillon cube, soy sauce, Accent, sugar, steak and vegetables together.
Quickly stir this other mixture into or over the meat mixture and thicken. Taste to your own; may need more salt.
Serve immediately!
Serve over rice.

title: chicken pesto
directions: Cut up chicken into cubes. Start cooking pasta. In frying pan, melt butter and mix in lemon juice. Place chicken into frying pan and sprinkle garlic salt and pepper on top. While chicken is cooking, place cream cheese and pesto in a saucepan. Melt over a low heat. Once everything is done, mix together. Serve immediately.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, butter and cheese.
Heat together until cheese is melted.
Add onion and potatoes to soup mixture and mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cauliflower sauce
directions: Cook butter, flour and milk until thick.
Add onion and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add paprika; cook until soft and red pink.

title: crusted corn pie
directions: Blend together cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Line bottom of 9-inch pie plate with 1/2 of the cracker crumb and butter mixture.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a saucepan; gradually add hot water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce to low heat, add milk and heat thoroughly. Stir often.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat with a wire whisk until foamy.
Top with marshmallows.
Makes 6 (6 ounce) servings.

title: everyday broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot oleo, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and broccoli is done, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookie(serves 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line baking sheets with parchment paper.
Place the butter in a large bowl and cream lightly with an electric mixer.
Add the sugars and beat on medium speed for about 2 minutes.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the vanilla and lemon juice and mix well.

title: caramel ring
directions: Place butter in 8-inch round dish.
Microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds until melted.
Sprinkle sugar over butter.
Add corn syrup. Stir well with fork.
Place 4-ounce drinking glass or 6-ounce custard cup, open side up in center of dish.
Sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Arrange biscuits over mixture in petal shape, squeezing to fit.
Microwave at Medium (5) 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove glass and invert onto serving plate.
Let dish stand over rolls a few minutes.

title: juanita's flour tortillas
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together and then work shortening into flour until mealy.
Start with 2 cups of very warm (but not hot) water.
Work in little by little small portions of water into the meaty mix until soft dough is achieved.
Roll the dough into baseball sized dough balls and let rest for 15 minutes.
Roll each little dough ball into a nice, round tortilla, with a rolling pin, turning the tortilla over several times.
Cook on a hot griddle (or in a hot skillet) without grease!
Turn when bubbles begin to appear and puff up; take out when both sides have been cooked.

title: red stuff
directions: Boil all together.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Strain out cinnamon, cloves and lemon.
Enjoy!
Great for the holidays.

title: souped up macaroni and beef
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Cook the macaroni and cheese according to the directions on the box.
Combine the meat and macaroni, adding the tomato sauce and water.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: no fat chicken and asparagus stir-fry
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, ginger wine, soy sauce and white pepper.
Stir in chicken.
Marinate 1/2 hour.
In frying pan, bring broth to boil.
Add asparagus and carrot.
use high heat until asparagus changes color.
Bring broth to boil.
Remove vegetables to platter.
Bring broth to boil.
Add chicken until done.
Stir in vegetables and oyster sauce.
Thicken with a little cornstarch, if needed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and water until creamy.
Blend in flour and nuts.
Take pinches of dough and, with hand, roll into finger shapes.
Bake at 350° until ends begin to turn light brown. When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: pot roast
directions: Wash roast and place in center of foil. Salt and pepper, and slice onion on top of roast. Wrap foil loosely around roast and place in a roaster pan, large enough to hold everything. Cook until will done in oven, at 450 degrees. When well done, remove foil. Spread 2 cans of Golden Mushroom Soup over the roast, rinse the cans with water, pouring this around the roast. Peel potatoes and cut in half, place then around the roast. Peel carrots and place around roast. Return to oven and cook until potatoes and carrots are done.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Mash ripe bananas with fork or blender until they are smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream maker and process. (We hand crank ice cream all summer long!
This is the best recipe for banana ice cream that I've ever tried.
You may substitute strawberries or fresh peaches, if you like!)

title: creamy cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix the ingredients and place in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: grannie's macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine cheese, onion, milk, soup and pimentos, mixing well with the macaroni.
Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Continue melted margarine and cracker crumbs, mixing well.
Spread over macaroni mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel mix
directions: Mix cereals, pretzels and nuts in large container.
Bring margarine, syrup and sugar to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add salt first, then soda.
Will foam.
Pour over mix.
Stir with wooden spoon until coated.
Bake on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in closed container.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cornflakes and coconut, mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: shrimp masala(pakistan)
directions: Grind together the garlic, ginger, coriander, cumin and red pepper to a paste.
Heat oil in a pan; add onion.
Saute onions. Add ground paste and cook until oil separates about 15 minutes on a low temperature.
Strain coconut.
Add coconut milk to the onions and bring to a boil, then simmer over medium low heat 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer until shrimp is done, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: southern party potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over potatoes into a 3-quart casserole.
Mix 1/4 cup butter and corn flakes.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 16.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: super bean bake
directions: Fry bacon and reserve 3 T of drippings.
Add onion and cook until limp.
Combine all ingredients, spoon mixture into shallow, 3 qt baking pan.
Bake uncovered in a 350 F oven for 1 hr.
(This could be placed in a slow cooker for 3-4 hrs)
Serves 12-14 people.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix water, shortening, salt and sugar.
When cool, beat in egg, then add yeast mixture.
Stir in flour.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours; shape and let rise 2 hours.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: sauerkraut stew
directions: Slice and brown sausage in Dutch oven.
Add coarsely chopped onion, peeled and sliced potatoes and carrots sliced 1/2 inch thick.
While these saute a bit, drain and rinse sauerkraut and peel and slice apples.
Add to pot with apple juice.
Cook on low until carrots are tender, about 2 hours.
One pound beef stew meat browned with sausage is tasty.
I like to add 2 to 3 tablespoons brown sugar.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line bottoms of 3 (9-inch) round cake pans with wax paper. Microwave chocolate and water in large microwavable bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring 1/2 way through heating time. Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. Beat margarine and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla. Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until smooth. Beat egg whites in another large bowl with electric mixer on high speed until stiff peaks form. Gently stir into batter. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center. Immediately run spatula between cakes and sides of pans. Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans. Remove wax paper. Cool completely on wire racks. Spread Coconut-Pecan Frosting between layers and over top of cake.

title: candied fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar,
beat
in
egg.
Stir
in dry ingredients.
Blend in
nuts and fruits.
Form into 1 1/2 inch logs.
Roll and
wrap in Saran or cling wrap.
Freeze and when ready to bake
cookies, slice thin and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 325° oven.	A delicious Christmas cookie.

title: onion pie
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Mix eggs and cream. Combine mixture with onions.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: This makes a neat prize for a baby shower.

title: pastrami dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown pepper, onion and rice in oil or margarine, 6 to 8 minutes.
Add consomme, 1/2 cup of water and mushrooms.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil 1 minute.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Serve hot!

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In a mug, put rum, lemon and cinnamon stick.
Place pat of butter in mug and pour in boiling water to fill mug.
Stir with stick to melt butter.

title: stirred custard
directions: Combine in a double boiler the eggs, sugar and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook in double boiler over hot water until mix coats the spoon.
Add vanilla and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts; save broth.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: christmas cake cookies
directions: Chop dates in chunks.
Cut cherries in quarters.
Slice pineapple thin.
Mix rest of ingredients together in order listed. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 150 to 170 cookies.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in glass loaf pan on High in microwave for 4 to 6 minutes or until no pink remains.
Stir once. Drain.
Layer Veg-All, then soup with Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
Add 1/4 cup water over casserole.
Cook, covered, on High 6 to 8 minutes.

title: wilton decorator icing
directions: Cream Crisco and oleo together.
Add powdered sugar one cup at a time, then add vanilla and milk.
Mix well.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a jar.
Shake and chill. Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss with the dressing and serve immediately.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes and grate after they have cooled completely. Combine the sour cream, onion, soup, butter and 1/2 of the cheese and add to the grated potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Place in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread the remainder of the cheese on top.
Sprinkle parsley over top, if desired, for color.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and cheese at room temperature.
Mix mayonnaise. Add salt and crab.
Spread on split muffins.
Freeze for 10 minutes.
Broil until bubbly and crisp.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and freeze.
Place in freezer until needed.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cream cheese, pudding and milk together until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In glass serving dish or dessert cups, layer filling and cookies alternately, starting and ending with cookies.
Chill until served.

title: patty's cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding and eggs; mix well. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry glazed fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Fold in glaze.
Chill one hour.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine eggs, flour, milk and salt in bowl.
Melt butter in glass pie plate in oven.
Remove and coat bottom and sides with melted butter.
Pour excess in bowl mixture.
Stir in.
Add blueberries.
Pour all mixture in pie plate.
Return to oven.

title: one bowl pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl.
Mix until blended, 3 minutes at medium speed.
Put into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan. Turn out on cake plate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut into pieces.
Mix with soup and peas and carrots.
Bake eat 400° for 20 minutes.
Add biscuits to top.
Bake for 10 minutes or until biscuits are light brown.

title: caramel surprise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package and use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove cake from oven and while still warm, use the tip of a wooden spoon and poke holes about 1 inch apart over surface of cake.
Meanwhile, open one can of frosting and heat in microwave for 30 seconds and stir.
Microwave 30 seconds longer or until frosting is thick but pourable.
Pour over top of cake while still warm and let cake soak up the frosting. Cool, then frost in pan with the other can of frosting.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter; cool.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: fancy, favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: In large pan, cook hamburger and onion over medium heat, slowly, until hamburger is no longer red.
Stir occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.
This is a rich, thick spaghetti sauce and leftover sauce is excellent served on hamburger buns for an unusual type Sloppy Joe sandwich.
Freezes well.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, eggs, flour, milk, vanilla and undrained pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Add oleo.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool and serve.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie
directions: Soften gelatin in the 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.
Beat egg yolks after separating them.
Mix yolks, milk, brown sugar, salt, pumpkin and spices in a pot.
Cook on low heat about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove pot from heat and stir in gelatin mixture.
Cool.

Set in refrigerator to chill for about 1 hour. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; then gradually add the 1/2 cup granulated sugar to the egg whites, beating until glossy. Fold egg white mixture into the pumpkin mixture until well blended.
Turn into baked pie shell and cool in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: praline kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees.
Beat egg white with salt lightly in electric mixer.	Beat in sugar and vanilla until light and smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields approximately 40-50 cookies.

title: monterey spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, beat egg.
Add sour cream, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Drain spaghetti; add to egg mixture with Monterey Jack cheese, spinach and half the onions.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; return to the oven for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: spring tea(refreshing!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in gallon pitcher.
Fill with water and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: apple pie sundae
directions: Place 2 small scoops ice cream in each dish.
Spoon in apple pie filling and top with crushed crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into chunks; cook in water to cover until done. Grease a casserole.
Spread in layers as follows:
squash, garlic powder, salt and pepper, cheese, onion and dressing.
End with cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sesame cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and almond extract; beat until well blended.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well to shape each cookie; press a ball of dough between your palms to make a 2-inch round.
In a small bowl beat egg yolks with water. Brush egg yolk mixture on one side of each round, then dip coated side in sesame seed.
Place cookies 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet, seeded side up.
Press down gently on each ball. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned at 350°.
Transfer cookies to wire rack and let them cool completely.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Very good dip!

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients together adding the cornbread mix last.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 30 to 45 minutes until lightly brown.
Overbaking makes them crunchy; to be chewy they must be barely done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; chill.
Slice angel food cake into 3 layers.
Put mixture between layers.
