Pour blueberry filling on top and dribble down sides.

title: beverly's tomato sauce
directions: Brown beef and sausage in a large dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
If extra liquid is needed add stewed tomatoes and spices.
Variation:
You may add zucchini and eggplant if desired.

title: applesaucy cookie surprises
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg. Mix dry ingredients and add 1/4 to 1/2 to creamed mixture. Then add applesauce and rest of flour mixture. Add chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 375° until dropped cookies just turn brown.

title: blue goose pie
directions: Place fruit in pie shell.
Mix dry ingredients.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain off fat.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions on the box.
Set aside.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, onion and bell pepper to hamburger meat.
Simmer over low heat until onions and bell pepper are tender.
Put all of the above in a casserole dish. This usually fits in a 8x11 rectangle dish or a 2-1/2 quart dish.
Stir in the macaroni and cheese and add the cheese to the top.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for about 30 minutes or until cheese starts to bubble.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in an unbaked pie shell for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Place rice in rectangle cake pan.
Pour bouillon over top. Stir.
Gently place pork chops on top.
Slice onion and arrange on pork chops.
Season to taste (salt and pepper).
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch blondies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Beat butter, brown sugar and white sugar in large bowl until creamy. Add eggs. Beat well. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, blending well. Stir in butterscotch chips and nuts. Spread in prepared pan. Bake 35 minutes or until top is golden brown and center is set. Cool completely in pan. Cut into bars.

title: disappearing chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 nine inch round pans.
Cream shortening, butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Do not rush this step as the cake is not nearly as good.
Blend in eggs.
In a seperate bowl, combine cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add alternately with milk to batter.
Blend well on medium speed. Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pans.

title: spicy pot roast
directions: Season roast with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Brown meat well on all sides in oil.
Add water and garlic.
Cover.
Simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until all vegetables are tender.
Thicken gravy, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add potatoes; cook until tender (but still firm).
Drain, cool, peel and chop.
Place eggs in saucepan; cover with cold water.
Bring water to a boil. Remove from heat; let eggs stand in hot water 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from hot water; cool, peel and chop.
In large bowl, combine potato, eggs, celery, onion, relish, garlic salt, celery salt, mustard, pepper and mayonnaise.
Mix well together; refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked beans(for a crowd)
directions: Put the beans in 4-gallon iron kettle.
Cover with water and boil 10 minutes over hot flame, stirring constantly.
Add more water.
Remove from fire and add the pork, molasses, mustard, salt and onion.
Cover with tightly fitting cast-iron lid.

title: apple bread
directions: Stir sugar into apples and let stand 30 minutes.
Stir flour, soda and cinnamon together in large bowl.
Beat together vanilla, oil and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Blend in apples and chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pans 15 minutes.
I prefer to use 3 loaf pans.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Place chocolate morsels in top of double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate melts.
Add noodles and peanuts, stirring well.
Drop chocolate mixture by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: cobblestone candy
directions: Melt chocolate over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Spread into foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Allow to stand until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 1 2/3 pounds.

title: red bean toss
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Blend mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl. Toss with bean mixture. Sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems.
Dice about 1/2 or less of stems. Place mushroom caps on foil covered cookie sheet.
In a mixing bowl, add sausage, stems, onions, egg, bread crumbs and cheese. Mix well.
Stuff caps with mixture.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan dump pineapple, then pie filling, then cake mix.
Over this cut up margarine; add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Cherry pie filling is also good.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and distribute evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread celery, eggs, peas, green pepper, onion and bacon over the lettuce.

title: shortbread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut the shortening into confectioners sugar as you do when cutting shortening into flour for pastry, then add flour mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
About halfway through the mixture (blend thoroughly), use your hands.
Chill until easy to handle, then roll out on lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into squares or diamonds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about an inch apart. Bake at 350° until a delicate brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Let cook until water is gone.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir until cheese has melted.
Add refried beans.
Picante sauce can be added at this point, if children like it.
Put a spoonful or two of the meat mixture on flat tortilla and roll up.
This meat mixture can also be used to make taco burgers or taco salad.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Slowly add milk.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell and cover.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup prior to serving, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: best ever tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and all sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour; measure and sift again with baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Space about 1/4-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Prick tops with fork. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cakes don't have to be completely browned on tops, but bottoms should.
Yield:
about 6 dozen 2-inch tea cakes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain broccoli; let cool.
Melt butter and let cool.
Mix broccoli, mayonnaise, onions, eggs, soup, butter and cheese together.
Mix in 1/2 cup of stuffing.
Pour remainder of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add fruits.
Place 1/2 in pan and refrigerate until set.
Remove; spread sour cream on jello mixture and then pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Chill until set.

title: mud flop(dessert)
directions: Crust:	Mix flour, butter and crushed pecans.
Press in pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add to softened butter, mixing well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Bake chicken at 350° until done.
Mix cream of chicken, mushroom, celery and onion soups together.
When chicken is ready, pour mixture over chicken, mixing some with chicken juices.
Put back in oven to bake for 1/2 hour.
Serve.

title: sesame glazed chicken
directions: Roast sesame seed in dry skillet over medium heat until lightly browned.
Stir or shake to prevent burning.
Place seeds in bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Marinate chicken in mixture 30 minutes.
Put chicken in bottom of broiler pan.
Pour mixture over.
Brown both sides under broiler, then bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: sue brayman's zucchini
directions: Grease baking dish.
Slice zucchini, sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Layer solidly in dish.
Add onion and green pepper.
Slice tomatoes on top.
Repeat.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cover for about 25 minutes.
Vary amount of ingredients according to number of people to be served.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare apples.
Add all ingredients.
Cook in pot until clear. Pour in pie shell.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: angel auntie's angel biscuits
directions: Preheat over 400°. Add yeast-water mixture to all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until mixed well.
Add more flour if needed and knead on floured surface.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pan.
Use what you want and place unused dough in covered container; put in refrigerator. Keeps several days.
Biscuits are best when allowed to rise 30 minutes before baking.
Bake 400° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: bacon wrapped pork loin
directions: Wrap bacon around pork loin. Use toothpicks to hold bacon to loin. Salt and pepper loin. Put loin in bowl or marinade dish. Pour 1/2 cup orange juice over pork loin. Add Worcestershire sauce. Marinate for 8 to 24 hours. Wrap loin in tinfoil and grill at 350°.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 45 minutes to 60 minutes.
Take chicken off bone.
In a saucepan mix celery soup with a can of water, chili powder and picante sauce to taste.
Bring to boil, then simmer on low.
Take off heat and add 1/4 cup of sour cream and chicken.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese and crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon walnut muffins
directions: Cream the sugar and softened butter or margarine until pale and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then the yogurt or buttermilk, lemon peel, salt, soda and walnuts.
Gradually add the flour, mixing until well blended.
Spoon into greased or paper lined 2 3/4-inch muffin cups. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes until springy to the touch.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, jello, syrup and water. Cook until thick. Let cool and pour over sliced strawberries in pie shells. Let set in refrigerator. Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot water chocolate cake
directions: Mix well together sugar, flour and cinnamon, set aside. In saucepan put oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to rapid boil. Add this to sugar
and flour.
Add buttermilk with soda dissolved in it.
Beat well.	Bake
at
400°	for
to
25 minutes in greased and floured 9
x
13-inch pan.
Let cool in pan.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: fat free banana bread
directions: Cream applesauce, prunes and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and add.
Add bananas and nuts.
Spray loaf pan with Pam and bake at 300° for 1 or 1 1/4 hours, until checks clean with toothpick.

title: maple creams
directions: Cook cream and syrup to 238°.
Pour on a cold slab; cool to lukewarm.
Work with spatula or paddle until mass holds its shape. Form into 3/4-inch balls; dip in melted chocolate.
Makes about 25 centers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meats, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and dry mustard.
Add applesauce and eggs and mix well. Rub 8 cup mold with shortening; sprinkle with 1/4 cup bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio dessert salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Boil for 3 minutes, then add other ingredients.
Mix and drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: pineapple pleasure
directions: Empty pineapple into well-greased casserole. Beat eggs and sugar, then flour. Mix well with pineapple. Put bread cubes on top of pineapple mixture. Pour melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. If it gets too brown, cover loosely with foil.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Add egg, milk and vanilla. Roll out on floured board to 1/16-inch thickness. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in water.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, salt and beaten egg yolks.
Stir and cook in double boiler until the consistency of custard.
Stir in the dissolved gelatin and grated lemon rind.
Cool these ingredients.
Whip 4 egg whites until stiff, then beat in 1/2 cup sugar very slowly.
In a separate bowl, beat heavy cream until stiff.
When the custard begins to thicken, beat with a wire whisk until it is fluffy. Fold in the egg whites.
Fold in the cream, reserving a portion for decorating the top of the pie.
Pour mixture into prepared pie shell.
Chill the pie thoroughly before serving.

title: old fashioned banana cake
directions: Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
Sift in large bowl the first five ingredients.
Mix canned milk, lemon juice, butter and bananas.
Add alternately to dry ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs. Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Frost.

title: easy blueberry dessert
directions: Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Tear 3/4 of angel food cake into pieces to fill dish.
Mix pudding according to directions, stir in Cool Whip.
Pour over cake and let set in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Keep chilled.
Serve.

title: mom's chocolate cream pie
directions: Pour evaporated milk into measuring cup.
Add regular milk to make 1 cup.
Then add 1/4 cup more milk.
Add egg yolks, sugar, flour, cocoa, salt and milk into blender.
Blend for a few seconds. Then add melted butter; blend again.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with juice, marshmallows, nuts and pistachio pudding.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate.
This recipe serves 6 to 10 persons.

title: george's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
sugars
and
shortening;
add
eggs and vanilla. Mix in dry ingredients, oats, pecans and raisins.
Shape into balls; flatten
slightly.	Bake
10 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 375°.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Serve with Stoned Wheat Thins.
(This can be doubled, tripled, whatever.)

title: carrot soup
directions: Combine carrots, onion and broth.
Cover and heat to boiling over high heat.
Reduce to low and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, uncover and cool mixture 10 minutes. Set aside about 8 carrot slices for garnish.
Pour mixture into blender or food processor.
Blend or process until finely chopped. Increase speed to blend or process until smooth.
Stop blender/processor and add cheese to carrot mixture.
Blend/process soup mixture until cheese is smooth.
Pour in bowls and garnish with carrot slices and dill sprigs.

title: beaufort stew
directions: In large pot, combine water, Old Bay seasoning, sliced lemon and sliced onion.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add sausage.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add corn; boil 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; boil 3 to 5 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Serve with baked or boiled potatoes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Boil pasta in salted water until tender; drain.
Mix pasta, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Add the cubed cheese and corned beef.
Pour into buttered casserole; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: one pan tuna and noodles
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, saute onion in margarine until soft. Add all other ingredients and boil gently until noodles are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add tuna and cheese and stir until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp fajitas(serves 8)
directions: In a bowl, combine all seasonings plus salt and pepper to taste. Toss shrimp in mixture.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour, soda, sugar and salt.
Set aside.

title: down-home chicken chowder
directions: In saucepan or large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Brown mushrooms and cook onion with thyme in drippings until tender. Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally. Easy!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
May also be used as a dessert.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until thick (will not get very thick); set aside.
Cool.
Whip the cream.
Add the pineapple, fruit cocktail, mandarin orange slices, marshmallows and mayonnaise.
Add this to the custard and freeze.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add rest and blend well.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: steamed shrimp ii
directions: Place margarine in saucepan and melt.
Add chopped vegetables and saute until tender.
Add shrimp and cool about 5 minutes.
Add beer; cover and steam about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt.
Stir constantly over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until syrup reaches 300°. Stir in peanuts.
Mix soda and vanilla in quickly.
Stir into candy (mixture will foam).
Quickly turn out into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Cool completely, then break into pieces.

title: carnell sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients and whisk.
Let meat marinate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: jerry's goulash
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add chili powder, corn, ketchup, tomato juice, barbecue sauce and Tabasco sauce and simmer 10 minutes. Cook noodles in 1 quart water. Add water and noodles to sauce. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with 3 cups liquid.
Use liquids from canned fruits and add water to make 3 cups.
Cool slightly and add fruits.
Refrigerate and decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Set aside to cool.
Make "toss salad" of lettuce, tomatoes, onion and pepper.
May add black olives if wish.
Add cooled hamburger and toss together.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain.
Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Combine this mixture and remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Toss.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: ham meat loaf
directions: Mix ground meats, bread crumbs, milk, egg, salt and pepper. Combine oleo and brown sugar and pour into baking dish or large loaf pan.
Place pineapple slices on top of sugar mixture.
Mold ham mixture on top of pineapple and drizzle pineapple juice over the loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done, basting occasionally with pan juices.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salts and pepper. Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Cook meatballs in skillet until brown on all sides; drain.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: Combine crushed graham crackers, sugar and melted butter. Mix with fork until moist and press into pie plate to make crust (reserve extra crumb mixture for top). Dissolve lemon jello in hot water and cream with cream cheese.
Add a few drops of yellow food coloring, if desired.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on box and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Put in pie crust and sprinkle with extra graham cracker crumbs.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix together rice and cream of chicken soup.
Spread on bottom of casserole dish.
Lay pieces of chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tex-mex dip(7 layers)
directions: This dish is assembled in layers.
Spread bean dip in 10-inch pie plate.
Mix next four ingredients and spread on top of layer one.
Mix next three ingredients and spread on top of layer two. Each of next four ingredients serves as a layer, in order found in ingredients list.
Serve with round taco chips.

title: moma's brownies
directions: Mix shortening, cocoa and margarine together over very low heat, stirring constantly; cool.
Beat eggs until light; stir in sugar, then chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes; cool.
Frost with Chocolate Butter Frosting.
Cut in squares.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and lemon juice. Add milk and mix well. Blend cornstarch in 1/2 cup sugar and add to mix.
Stir in blueberries. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.
Makes 2 pies. A graham cracker crust or pastry crust can be used.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix butter, sugar, shortening and eggs in large bowl for 3 minutes.
Stop.
Add the nuts, bananas and flour mixture.
Beat until smooth, about 1 minute.
Put in bread pan and bake 1 hour or until done in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans at 350°.
Store overnight before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water to soften.
Meanwhile cook strawberries and sugar over a low heat for 15 minutes, until thickened.
Remove from heat and add softened gelatin, mixing well. Cool this mixture completely.
Stiffly beat egg whites.
In another bowl whip the cream and cognac together.
Stir gelatin mixture with the cream, then fold in the egg whites.
Mix well and chill. Serves 10.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute green onion in oil in a large nonstick saucepan.
Add chicken stock, milk and potatoes.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 12 minutes.
Add corn and cook 1 minute more.
Remove 2 cups of the chowder to a food processor, puree and return to saucepan.
Stir in dry milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: picnic fruit punch
directions: Combine the juices in a large container and refrigerate. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and orange slices. Makes 5 quarts.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, celery and onion until hamburger is light brown, then drain.
Pour water on rice and add salt in greased 2-quart casserole.
Stir in hamburger, soup, mushrooms, sugar, soy sauce and margarine.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes; stir.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.
Stir in noodles; serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chocolate nutty bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, over low heat, melt 1 cup chips with butter; remove from heat.
Add Bisquick mix, sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in the nuts and the remaining chips.
Turn into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until nutties begin to pull away from the sides of pan.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.
Store tightly covered.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, melted butter and chopped pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Brush chicken with part of melted margarine.
Place flour and chicken in bag.
Shake to coat.
Arrange chicken in baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining margarine, honey, lemon juice and soy sauce in saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake an additional 30 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: tyler's tempting honey-sesame wings
directions: Clean wings and discard tips.
Combine all ingredients except sesame seed in a large bowl or pan.
Marinate wings in honey-Dijon mixture for at least 1 hour.
Make sure wings are covered with mixture.
Turn wings while marinating.
Toast sesame seed at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
(Give the pan of seed a shake now and then so they don't burn.)
Dip chicken wings in seed.
Broil wings for about 20 minutes, turning them every 5 minutes.

title: chocolate logan cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl. In saucepan, mix oleo, water and Crisco. Bring to a rapid boil. Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix buttermilk, eggs and soda together and then add to the other ingredients. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. (Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured cake pan.)

title: mayonnaise
directions: Blend on low speed for 15 seconds, then pour oil in while it is going.
Beat for 1 minute; scrape, then reblend.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Fold in condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Chill.

title: corn flake squares
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup until it comes to a boil.
Take off. Add peanut butter.
Stir well until smooth.
Add 5 cups corn flakes.
Spread into a buttered pan to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: microwave vegetable medley
directions: Slice julienne the squash, green pepper, zucchini and carrots. Slice onions in rounds.
Mix together in microwaveproof baking dish. Dot with butter.
Add about 1/4 cup water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Seasoning salt to taste.
Sprinkle with 1 pack of Equal.
Cover with plastic wrap, leaving a small opening. Microwave 13 to 14 minutes, depending on size of your dish.
Drain liquid.
Serve.

title: cherry confetti cake
directions: In large bowl, cream margarine, adding sugar gradually until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs one at a time into creamed mixture.
Alternately add flour and baking powder and milk to above creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and cherries.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place crackers in plastic bag and roll fine with rolling pin. Sprinkle salt over hamburg.
Cut in with spoon and mix in one cup of milk.
Add cracker crumbs.
Mix in.
Add one egg, beaten, and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix well.
If too dry, add a little more milk. Bake in glass bread pan or greased bread tin.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix 1/2 cup cheese crackers in with broccoli.
Layer remaining ingredients in casserole dish, top with remaining cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat together all ingredients and put into loaf pan.
If desired, pour one 8 ounce can tomato sauce over mixture or cover with 2 strips of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kraut salad
directions: Run cold water over kraut and drain well.
Mix everything except sugar and vinegar together.
Mix sugar and vinegar, stirring to dissolve sugar; pour over mixture and mix well.
Keep refrigerated and serve well chilled.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven until tests done.

title: white cucumber salad
directions: Slice peeled cucumbers very thin.
For each large cuke, add a tablespoon of grated onion to 1/2 cup of mayonnaise mixture. Arrange a layer of cukes in a shallow bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and spread with mayonnaise mixture.
Continue until all is used, ending with mayo on top.
Cover and place in refrigerator 12 to 14 hours before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Place in greased oblong pan. Crush corn flakes; mix with oleo.
Spread flakes on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie supreme
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating until thick.
Add pumpkin, milk, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger, stirring well.
Pour pumpkin mixture into top of a double boiler and bring water to a boil.
Cook over water until mixture is thickened.
Soften gelatin in cold water, add to pumpkin mixture, stirring well.
Set mixture aside to cool. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until foamy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Chill.
Beat whipping cream until foamy, gradually add powdered sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Spread whipping cream over filling.
Garnish with additional cinnamon, if desired.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Pound the chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Add all other ingredients.
Roll up and dredge through flour, 1 beaten egg and then crushed corn flakes.
Line in a shallow pan, seam side down. Let stand overnight or at least 1 hour in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, pour 1/2 cup melted butter and 1/2 cup dry white wine or chicken broth over meat, carefully not disturb the crumbs. Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil, baste with liquid and cook 1/2 hour longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: souped up pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in egg and bread crumbs.
Brown in skillet. Layer pork chops in roaster pan.
Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can cream of celery soup together.
Spoon over top of pork chops.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, covered.
Take out and top with Mozzarella cheese and bake 1 hour more.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Boil 1 cup of water; add to the Jell-O.
Stir until mixed in good, then add sour cream and strawberries; mix that well.
Pour into molds and let chill.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes, pat dry and prick a few times with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cut a thin slice off the top. Carefully scoop out the pulp and put in bowl.

title: macaroni and cheese soup
directions: Cook macaroni per directions; drain.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour and cheese sauce from dinner mix.
Stir in broth and beer. Cook and stir until thickened.
Add vegetables and ham.
Cook and stir until heated.
Stir in cooked macaroni.

title: lilco lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine or butter until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir beef until light brown. Drain off fat.
Add onions and green pepper and cook and stir until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: impossible pie(custard pie made in blender makes own crust.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put ingredients into blender for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour pie pan.
Pour ingredients in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Can substitute and use: sugar-free Jell-O, nonfat cottage cheese and light Cool Whip.

title: apple pie
directions: In a 9-inch pie pan, place your favorite pastry dough. Sprinkle half of the combined sugar, flour and spices onto pastry. Heap apples in the pastry and sprinkle with remaining sugar and flour mixture.
Dot with butter.
Place top pastry.
Brush with egg and make slits to vent.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: pimento cream cheese
directions: Let cheese soften.
Mix all ingredients well with mixer.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain grease from frying pan.
Add the rest of ingredients and stir it all together. Let it simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Put in long baking dish or casserole dish and bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken and honey
directions: Melt butter; add honey, mustard and curry powder.
Pour over chicken parts.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Baste often.

title: raisin pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except raisins.
Roll raisins in the 1/2 cup flour.
Add to batter.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours in 275° oven, in well-greased tube pan.
This makes a large cake and will keep a long time.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press rolls onto an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread over baked rolls.
Spread vegetables over cheese mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and press vegetables into cheese mixture.
Chill, covered, 3 to 4 hours.
Cut, serve and enjoy.

title: chunky vegetable soup
directions: Add to potato mixture.
Salt to taste.
Cook slowly for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: jiffy-quick custards
directions: Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour in 6 to 8 thin custard cups.
Place cups in a saucepan or deep frying pan with tight fitting lid.
Pour tap water in pan.
Water should be level with custards.
Bring water to full boil; immediately turn off heat and cover pan.
Let custards stand, covered, 6 minutes or until knife inserted in center of custard comes out clean.
Remove cup from water.
Cool and chill.

title: pineapple fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar and stir well. Add eggs, milk and pineapple, stir until smooth.
Heat 3 to 4-inches of oil to 375°.
Carefully drop batter by heaping tablespoonful into hot oil.
Cook about 1 minute or until golden on one side.
Turn and cook other side about 1 minute.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 3 dozen.
